WEBVTT

00:13.347 --> 00:14.348
[buzzer beeps]

00:17.435 --> 00:19.353
- [crowd cheering]
- [rhythmic thudding]

00:19.437 --> 00:21.355
[crowd chanting] <i>Roots run deep.</i>

00:21.439 --> 00:23.315
<i>Roots run deep.</i>

00:23.399 --> 00:25.359
<i>Roots run deep.</i>

00:25.443 --> 00:27.361
<i>Roots run deep.</i>

00:27.445 --> 00:29.280
<i>Roots run deep.</i>

00:29.363 --> 00:30.781
<i>- Roots run deep.</i>
- [thudding stops]

00:31.407 --> 00:32.908
<i>Roots run deep.</i> [cheering]

00:32.992 --> 00:34.160
<i>Roots run deep.</i>

00:34.243 --> 00:35.494
<i>Roots run deep.</i>

00:35.578 --> 00:37.037
<i>Roots run deep.</i>

00:37.121 --> 00:39.206
- [Mom] Will!
- Come on, Mom. We're almost there.

00:39.290 --> 00:41.333
- [Mom] Will! You're so fast.
- Mom, there it is.

00:41.417 --> 00:43.294
[Mom] I can't keep up.
You need to be in the Olympics.

00:43.377 --> 00:45.087
Let's go, Mom. We're so close.

00:45.171 --> 00:48.048
[Will] Thank you for taking me
to see Jett's new billboard.

00:48.132 --> 00:51.802
- Jett's huge!
- [Mom] Will, say "cheese."

00:51.886 --> 00:53.929
- Will for three. [chuckles]
- [Mom chuckles] Ah, ah, ah.

00:54.013 --> 00:55.973
Okay, boy, don't be doing
all of that now.

00:56.056 --> 00:58.517
All right.
Guess it's time to go.

00:58.601 --> 00:59.810
You have to go to work, right?

00:59.894 --> 01:01.687
[Mom] Whoa, whoa, whoa.
[exhales] One second.

01:01.771 --> 01:03.063
- Wait, turn it around.
- [camera beeps]

01:03.147 --> 01:04.690
I got it! There we go. Okay.

01:04.774 --> 01:06.942
How about you and I

01:07.026 --> 01:10.613
watch the Thorns
from inside the stadium?

01:10.696 --> 01:12.823
'Cause I'm taking my baby

01:12.907 --> 01:17.578
to see his very first,
yep, roarball game!

01:17.661 --> 01:18.496
[exclaims]

01:18.579 --> 01:19.705
[stammers] What?

01:19.789 --> 01:21.791
[gasps]

01:21.874 --> 01:22.875
Is this for real?

01:22.958 --> 01:24.960
I mean... [chuckles]
...unless you're busy?

01:25.044 --> 01:27.004
- [sobs]
- Oh, baby.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.173
- Aw, it's okay.
- Thank you.

01:29.256 --> 01:32.426
Thank you so much.
I love you, Mom.

01:32.510 --> 01:34.345
I love you too, Will.

01:34.428 --> 01:35.554
Let's go, Mom. Come on.

01:35.638 --> 01:36.972
- Roots run deep.
- [fan] Yeah, let's go!

01:37.056 --> 01:39.517
Oh. It's right here.
Right here. Come on.

01:39.600 --> 01:41.227
Mom, stop it.

01:41.310 --> 01:43.395
[both] Whoo! Let's go!

01:43.479 --> 01:44.522
Whoo! Let's go!

01:44.605 --> 01:46.398
[announcer]
<i>Welcome to the Greenhouse!</i>

01:46.482 --> 01:48.567
- It's starting!
- [buzzer beeps]

01:51.195 --> 01:54.615
[announcer] <i>Are you ready?</i>

01:56.492 --> 01:58.244
- [voice 1] <i>Who is the GOAT?</i>
- [voice 2] <i>Who is the GOAT?</i>

01:58.327 --> 01:59.954
- [voice 3] <i>Who's the GOAT?</i>
- [voice 4] <i>Who's the GOAT?</i>

02:00.037 --> 02:02.540
[voice 2] <i>Who is truly the GOAT?</i>

02:02.623 --> 02:04.750
♪ <i>Yeah, thinkin' that</i>
<i>It happened overnight </i>♪

02:04.834 --> 02:05.668
♪ <i>It didn't </i>♪

02:05.751 --> 02:07.628
♪ <i>In it for the long-haul flight</i>
<i>Committed </i>♪

02:07.711 --> 02:08.963
♪ <i>Look, wait </i>♪

02:10.631 --> 02:12.049
[roars]

02:12.132 --> 02:15.135
[announcer] <i>Introducing</i>
<i>Vineland's very own,</i>

02:15.219 --> 02:18.973
<i>the hometown hero,</i>
<i>a five-time all-star,</i>

02:19.056 --> 02:20.683
<i>Jett Fillmore.</i>

02:20.766 --> 02:23.143
- Yeah! Let's go, Vineland.
- [crowd cheering]

02:23.227 --> 02:26.814
Let's go, Jett! [chuckles]

02:26.897 --> 02:29.024
Having a good time, Will? Baby?

02:29.108 --> 02:30.359
[Will gasps]

02:32.695 --> 02:34.363
[Will] That's gonna be me, Mom.

02:35.239 --> 02:36.407
When I get big,

02:37.157 --> 02:39.285
I'm gonna be just like her.

02:47.585 --> 02:48.752
[upbeat music playing]

02:52.256 --> 02:53.632
[horns honking]

02:54.758 --> 02:55.759
[Will pants]

02:55.843 --> 02:57.011
One... Yeah!

02:57.094 --> 02:59.430
It's the power of the mind.
Your body's not tired.

02:59.513 --> 03:01.473
You can take a break.
Don't take a break.

03:02.391 --> 03:04.894
[panting]

03:05.436 --> 03:06.437
You got this.

03:07.771 --> 03:09.023
Keep pushing.

03:09.106 --> 03:11.525
- Keep pushing.
- [music ends]

03:11.609 --> 03:13.235
- [chuckling]
- [yelps]

03:13.319 --> 03:14.153
[gerbil] I'm okay!

03:14.236 --> 03:15.237
[Will grunts]

03:15.321 --> 03:16.655
Hey, Will. Are you working out?

03:16.739 --> 03:18.324
Hey, Theo. You know it.

03:18.407 --> 03:21.452
Jett Fillmore doesn't take
a day off, and neither do I.

03:21.535 --> 03:23.287
My dad said
you can't play roarball

03:23.370 --> 03:24.538
'cause you're too small.

03:24.622 --> 03:26.916
[Will groans]
Everyone says that, Theo.

03:26.999 --> 03:28.292
When I'm on the Thorns,

03:28.375 --> 03:31.003
you'll be courtside,
my bro-dent. [chuckles]

03:31.086 --> 03:32.254
Heck, yeah.

03:32.338 --> 03:33.339
Go, Thorns! [chuckles]

03:33.422 --> 03:34.632
[phone beeps]

03:35.382 --> 03:37.301
[Will] No rest for the ballers.

03:42.014 --> 03:43.849
Hey! Will!

03:44.350 --> 03:47.937
I hope you're not trying to
sneak out... [chuckles]

03:48.020 --> 03:50.230
...without paying your rent.

03:50.314 --> 03:52.483
Ooh. Yeah. Um...

03:52.566 --> 03:53.943
I'll get it to you
as soon as you,

03:54.026 --> 03:55.945
uh, fix those holes
in the ceiling.

03:56.028 --> 03:57.863
What holes? [screams]

03:57.947 --> 03:59.490
Gotta go to work.
Catch you later, Frank.

03:59.573 --> 04:01.033
[grunting] Will!

04:01.116 --> 04:02.701
[horn honks]

04:03.369 --> 04:05.037
Good morning, Vineland!

04:05.120 --> 04:07.039
[commuter] Whoever said that,
be quiet, please.

04:10.668 --> 04:11.794
[Will] Roots run deep!

04:11.877 --> 04:13.712
[all] Roots run deep!

04:13.796 --> 04:14.880
<i>Welcome back.</i>

04:14.964 --> 04:17.216
<i>Tonight,</i>
<i>it's Jett Fillmore, the vet,</i>

04:17.299 --> 04:19.927
<i>taking on Mane Attraction,</i>
<i>the champ.</i>

04:20.010 --> 04:22.221
<i>The GOAT debate starts here.</i>

04:22.304 --> 04:23.889
<i>Thorns versus Magma.</i>

04:23.973 --> 04:25.140
Go Magma!

04:25.224 --> 04:26.433
Go Shivers!

04:26.517 --> 04:29.269
Yeah, go whoever is playing
the Thorns. I-I don't care.

04:29.353 --> 04:30.604
Gerald!

04:30.688 --> 04:31.939
I'm gonna kick you out

04:32.022 --> 04:34.149
if you keep wearing
the other teams' jerseys.

04:34.233 --> 04:35.567
Carol, I'm the ultimate hater.

04:35.651 --> 04:36.819
No pie for you.

04:36.902 --> 04:38.737
Sheep. She took my pie. [grunts]

04:38.821 --> 04:41.740
The Thorns have broken his heart
one too many times.

04:41.824 --> 04:43.534
This is Vineland, Gerald.

04:43.617 --> 04:46.161
We never give up.
We've always got hope.

04:46.245 --> 04:49.373
The Thorns, they just need
to draft your boy.

04:49.456 --> 04:51.417
I'll turn things around
real quick.

04:51.500 --> 04:52.918
So, they're drafting
delivery goats now?

04:53.002 --> 04:53.919
[scoffs, chuckles]

04:54.003 --> 04:55.671
[Carol]
I need one to deliver food.

04:55.754 --> 04:58.590
Ooh! About that, Ms. Carol,
uh, can I get a raise?

04:58.674 --> 04:59.883
You want a raise?

04:59.967 --> 05:02.219
Tell the Thorns
to win a few games

05:02.302 --> 05:04.013
so we can get the crowds
back in here.

05:04.096 --> 05:06.390
I remember when
Jett was a rookie.

05:06.473 --> 05:08.058
This place used to be full.

05:08.142 --> 05:10.436
Before we realized she was
never gonna win us a Claw?

05:10.519 --> 05:12.146
Uh, Carol, can I have
my pie back, please?

05:12.229 --> 05:15.065
Keep talking. I'll cut you off
from ice cream too.

05:15.149 --> 05:17.317
- Be careful with these.
- Oh. Got it.

05:18.152 --> 05:20.070
Oh. Moe needs more coffee,

05:20.154 --> 05:22.239
and the out-of-towners,
they want their check.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.867
How do you always do that?
Freaks me out every time.

05:24.950 --> 05:27.244
Hey, I'm a goat.
I see everything.

05:27.327 --> 05:29.121
["Best Day" playing]

05:31.040 --> 05:32.374
- Pass it, Will.
- Okay!

05:32.458 --> 05:34.626
- Hey, guys.
- Got it! See you later, Will!

05:35.210 --> 05:36.920
[announcer]
<i>Thorns are already down by 20.</i>

05:37.004 --> 05:38.005
Oh, come on.

05:38.088 --> 05:40.132
[customer 1] Up here. [trumpets]

05:40.215 --> 05:41.633
All right. Let's do this.

05:42.509 --> 05:45.888
♪ <i>No worries up inside my mind </i>♪

05:45.971 --> 05:47.556
- [customer 1] Thank you.
- I got you.

05:47.639 --> 05:49.683
♪ <i>This is the best day</i>
<i>Of my life</i> ♪

05:51.185 --> 05:52.936
[groans, blows raspberries]

06:00.069 --> 06:01.904
♪ <i>This is the best day</i>
<i>Of my life</i> ♪

06:04.406 --> 06:06.200
♪ <i>This is the best day</i>
<i>Of my life</i> ♪

06:06.283 --> 06:07.826
Step back. Yes!

06:07.910 --> 06:08.869
[cheering]

06:08.952 --> 06:10.662
- [customer 2] Thank you.
- [customer 3] Thank you.

06:10.746 --> 06:12.247
- [customer 4] Thank you.
- [customer 5] Thank you.

06:12.748 --> 06:14.583
- Here you go.
- Appreciate you.

06:14.666 --> 06:16.043
[screams]

06:16.126 --> 06:17.127
[chuckling]

06:17.211 --> 06:18.253
♪ <i>This is the best day</i>
<i>Of my life</i> ♪

06:18.337 --> 06:19.338
[music ends]

06:19.880 --> 06:21.757
My mammal. Finally, bro.

06:21.840 --> 06:23.801
Chill, Daryl.
You ordered a water.

06:23.884 --> 06:25.886
Water is food too, bro.

06:25.969 --> 06:27.221
[Will] So, Hannah,
how's Jett doing?

06:27.304 --> 06:29.431
Mane's kind of
working Jett tonight.

06:29.515 --> 06:32.392
I hate to say it,
she might be washed.

06:32.476 --> 06:34.686
You serious? Jett can handle
that one-trick pony.

06:34.770 --> 06:38.190
Um, is his one trick
being the best at roarball?

06:38.273 --> 06:40.275
He's got the shooting,
the passing...

06:40.359 --> 06:41.610
Picture-perfect pecs.

06:41.693 --> 06:43.654
Luxurious locks.

06:43.737 --> 06:44.905
Mane is pretty much him.

06:44.988 --> 06:47.950
- [commentator] <i>Oh, my!</i>
- [both exclaim]

06:48.033 --> 06:49.660
<i>- Mane Attraction just put...</i>
- On her head!

06:49.743 --> 06:51.370
<i>...the former number-one pick,</i>
<i>Olivia Burke...</i>

06:51.453 --> 06:53.205
- That's not good.
<i>- ...on a poster.</i>

06:53.288 --> 06:54.873
- [phone beeps]
- [gasps] No way.

06:54.957 --> 06:57.084
[Will] Oh,
there's already memes?

06:57.167 --> 06:59.378
Oh, "poster child"?
Now, that's rough.

06:59.461 --> 07:01.296
Yeah, that was so not cool.

07:01.380 --> 07:03.632
[sighs] All right. I'm out.

07:03.715 --> 07:04.758
I'm gonna go train at the Cage.

07:04.842 --> 07:07.219
What? You're not gonna
watch the game with us?

07:07.302 --> 07:09.513
Nah, I gotta go
while the Cage is empty,

07:09.596 --> 07:11.765
'cause after the game,
you know it's gonna fill up.

07:11.849 --> 07:14.434
Do not let Grizz catch you.
[slurps]

07:14.518 --> 07:15.519
Oh, I won't.

07:16.228 --> 07:19.439
[crowd members]
Roots run deep. Roots run deep.

07:19.523 --> 07:21.817
[melancholy music playing]

07:24.653 --> 07:25.904
[exhales]

07:36.874 --> 07:38.208
Step back. Jett!

07:38.292 --> 07:39.960
[cheering]

07:40.043 --> 07:42.504
The crowd goes wild.

07:42.588 --> 07:44.464
["Parade" playing]

07:44.548 --> 07:46.175
♪ <i>Ooh</i> ♪

07:47.092 --> 07:50.262
♪ <i>It won't rain on my parade</i> ♪

07:51.680 --> 07:56.518
♪ <i>Oh, let it rain, ooh</i> ♪

08:03.609 --> 08:05.027
[cheers]

08:05.110 --> 08:06.987
Another one. [cheers]

08:07.571 --> 08:10.699
With only five seconds left,
the ball goes to Harris.

08:10.782 --> 08:12.159
He's all alone.

08:12.242 --> 08:14.912
Three, two, one...

08:14.995 --> 08:16.330
[music ends]

08:18.415 --> 08:19.541
[sighs]

08:21.126 --> 08:22.753
What's going on here, folks?

08:22.836 --> 08:24.129
They're resetting the clock?

08:24.213 --> 08:25.339
Don't question it.

08:25.422 --> 08:27.257
He's got time for one more shot.

08:27.341 --> 08:29.176
Three, two, one...

08:29.259 --> 08:30.844
[dramatic music playing]

08:35.182 --> 08:36.600
- [horn blares]
- [crowd cheering]

08:36.683 --> 08:38.143
[kisses]

08:38.227 --> 08:42.481
[crowd members] <i>Roots run deep.</i>
<i>Roots run deep. Roots run deep.</i>

08:42.564 --> 08:43.899
<i>Roots run deep.</i>

08:43.982 --> 08:46.318
One day, baby. [kisses] One day.

08:48.403 --> 08:50.322
[exclaims]

08:51.448 --> 08:53.367
[chuckling]

08:53.450 --> 08:55.327
Get that weak sauce
up out of here.

08:55.410 --> 08:57.621
Yo, what's your problem, Grizz?

08:57.704 --> 08:59.581
Every day you're here.

08:59.665 --> 09:02.084
Every day I gotta kick you out.

09:02.167 --> 09:04.044
I mean,
what are the rules, y'all?

09:04.127 --> 09:06.129
[all] Smalls can't ball.

09:06.213 --> 09:08.548
First off, I'm not a small.
I'm a medium.

09:08.632 --> 09:10.592
- What? Medium fries?
- [chuckling]

09:10.676 --> 09:13.136
You will never make it
into Roar.

09:13.220 --> 09:15.180
I mean, come on. Let me run.

09:15.264 --> 09:17.140
I'm better than
half of y'all anyways.

09:17.224 --> 09:18.725
Let me show you what I got.

09:18.809 --> 09:20.560
[scoffs] Ball me.

09:21.061 --> 09:23.730
Only thing you're running
is off this court.

09:24.898 --> 09:26.316
Now get out of here.

09:26.400 --> 09:27.985
[scoffs] Whatever.

09:28.068 --> 09:30.404
Good night, Shirley.
You're in my house now.

09:30.487 --> 09:32.030
[players cheering]

09:32.114 --> 09:33.532
[commentator]
<i>And that's the game.</i>

09:33.615 --> 09:34.825
<i>Thorns lose by 26.</i>

09:34.908 --> 09:36.576
Clock's ticking, Jett.

09:36.660 --> 09:39.871
Jett, Jett, Jett,
hey, can you sign this for me?

09:39.955 --> 09:42.833
Of course. Anything for a fan.

09:42.916 --> 09:43.917
There you go, kid.

09:44.001 --> 09:45.294
Thanks, Jett.

09:46.086 --> 09:47.754
Why can't you win
a championship?

09:48.672 --> 09:50.090
Retire already!

09:50.173 --> 09:51.341
Jett, could we take a photo?

09:51.425 --> 09:52.843
Jett, third loss in a row.

09:52.926 --> 09:54.886
- How does it feel?
- Flo? Where's Flo?

09:54.970 --> 09:56.471
- When are we gonna stop sucking?
- Flo!

09:56.555 --> 09:57.848
Hey. Flo?

09:57.931 --> 09:59.099
Who's seen Flo?

09:59.182 --> 10:00.517
[growls]

10:00.600 --> 10:02.769
["Mamacitas" playing]

10:02.853 --> 10:04.896
[inhales deeply, moans]

10:04.980 --> 10:06.940
[grunting]

10:08.317 --> 10:09.943
[snorts, exhales]

10:10.027 --> 10:11.028
[chuckles]

10:11.111 --> 10:12.946
Hey, there, grumpy cat.

10:13.947 --> 10:15.032
[growling]

10:15.824 --> 10:17.743
- How'd the game end?
- [all scream]

10:17.826 --> 10:19.077
I stopped watching

10:19.161 --> 10:21.997
and punched myself
in the face instead. [laughs]

10:22.080 --> 10:23.915
You think this is funny?

10:23.999 --> 10:25.876
You're the team owner, Flo.

10:25.959 --> 10:27.502
How am I supposed to win

10:27.586 --> 10:30.672
when you've got me surrounded
by head cases and has-beens?

10:30.756 --> 10:32.257
Hey, I'm working on it.

10:32.341 --> 10:34.009
We don't even have
a sixth player, Flo,

10:34.092 --> 10:35.177
but you got your hooves done.

10:35.260 --> 10:39.181
Listen here, Jett,
free agents aren't free. Okay?

10:39.264 --> 10:41.767
So unless you have
a sixth player in mind

10:41.850 --> 10:43.268
who can fill an arena

10:43.352 --> 10:45.562
and doesn't want
a big, fat check,

10:45.645 --> 10:48.565
I'm gonna get back
to my mud bath, okay?

10:48.648 --> 10:50.192
Oh, that is hogwash.

10:50.275 --> 10:52.110
It's your job to figure it out.

10:52.194 --> 10:53.570
Trade players, sell the team...

10:53.653 --> 10:57.449
I don't care what you got to do.
Just do it. Now.

10:57.532 --> 11:00.327
Careful what you wish for, Jett.

11:00.410 --> 11:02.162
[thudding]

11:02.996 --> 11:03.997
[gasps]

11:04.081 --> 11:05.457
[screams, groans]

11:05.957 --> 11:07.000
He's fine.

11:08.543 --> 11:11.046
[atmospheric music playing]

11:24.393 --> 11:27.312
Hey, I'm driving here.
Get out of the road, you medium.

11:27.396 --> 11:29.189
[whispers] Keep it down.
Why are you so loud?

11:30.857 --> 11:31.858
[groans]

11:32.776 --> 11:34.736
[Frank] Hello, William.

11:34.820 --> 11:36.655
Hey, Frank. How are you?

11:36.738 --> 11:40.158
Would you happen to have
that rent?

11:40.242 --> 11:42.828
Oh. Oh, yeah, yeah.
Right. Right.

11:42.911 --> 11:45.163
Frank, I got you.
It's all right here.

11:45.247 --> 11:46.581
I meant to give it to you
today actually.

11:46.665 --> 11:47.666
22, 23...

11:47.749 --> 11:50.836
This is not actual money,
this piece of paper.

11:50.919 --> 11:52.045
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

11:52.129 --> 11:54.381
What about last month's
and the month before?

11:54.423 --> 11:57.384
Frank, it's me. Come on.

11:57.467 --> 12:00.429
I just need a little more time.

12:00.512 --> 12:02.639
You had time, Will.

12:03.348 --> 12:05.016
I got mouths to feed.

12:05.100 --> 12:06.852
I don't need one more.

12:06.935 --> 12:07.853
- Hey, Will.
- Hey, Will.

12:07.936 --> 12:09.396
- Hey, Will.
- Hey, Will.

12:09.479 --> 12:12.107
- Hey, guys.
- Hey, Will. Hey, Will.

12:12.190 --> 12:14.151
Hey, Will. Hey, Will. Hey, Will.

12:14.234 --> 12:15.235
[Will] Y'all are still awake?

12:15.318 --> 12:17.112
- Hey, Will.
- Oh, what's up, Theo?

12:17.195 --> 12:18.905
Did they let you play
at the Cage today?

12:18.989 --> 12:20.490
You know me. I'm working on it.

12:20.574 --> 12:21.700
That's a lot of kids.

12:21.783 --> 12:23.201
Indeed it is.

12:23.285 --> 12:24.536
I'm sorry, kiddo.

12:24.619 --> 12:27.414
Look, get me my rent money
by tomorrow

12:27.497 --> 12:29.875
or I gotta rent the room to
somebody else.

12:29.958 --> 12:30.959
Capisce?

12:31.042 --> 12:32.043
Will, I forgot to tell you--

12:32.127 --> 12:33.503
[Frank] Hey, kids, come on.
Get in the tub.

12:33.587 --> 12:34.754
- Here we go, here we go.
- [sighs]

12:41.928 --> 12:43.722
[sighs] Whatever.

12:45.557 --> 12:46.558
<i>You need money?</i>

12:46.641 --> 12:47.642
<i>Well, you're in luck</i>

12:47.726 --> 12:50.312
<i>'cause you can start earning</i>
<i>up to 300 bucks per day.</i>

12:50.395 --> 12:54.774
<i>How? By trading crypto</i>
<i>on BigBroncoCrypto...</i>

12:55.275 --> 12:58.236
[wife] Frank,
I'm pregnant again.

12:58.320 --> 13:01.072
[Frank]
That's amazing, sweetheart.

13:01.156 --> 13:05.577
[chuckling] You know,
we needed another one of those.

13:05.660 --> 13:07.120
- Hey, Will...
- [knocking on wall]

13:07.204 --> 13:09.122
...gonna need that rent money.

13:20.800 --> 13:22.636
[upbeat music playing]

13:22.719 --> 13:26.306
♪ <i>You hoopin', we hoopin'</i>
<i>You shootin', I'm shootin' </i>♪

13:26.389 --> 13:28.308
- ♪<i>That glass, we crashin' </i>♪
- ♪ <i>Say what</i> ♪

13:28.391 --> 13:29.976
- ♪ <i>That pass, fantastic</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Okay </i>♪

13:31.228 --> 13:33.146
♪ <i>You'd better</i>
<i>Tie them shoes up </i>♪

13:33.230 --> 13:34.314
- [music ends]
- [Will] Boom!

13:34.397 --> 13:36.024
Check these out.

13:36.107 --> 13:39.319
Vineland green, Fillmore Fours,
in the flesh.

13:39.402 --> 13:41.404
Jett wore these
in the Furball game.

13:41.488 --> 13:43.657
Normally,
these sell for around six...

13:43.740 --> 13:46.576
- [inhales deeply]
- ...but I'll give it to you

13:46.660 --> 13:47.661
for five.

13:47.744 --> 13:50.288
- No, not the Fours.
- [exhales deeply]

13:50.372 --> 13:52.207
Oh, I wanted those.

13:52.290 --> 13:53.667
But you're broke.

13:53.750 --> 13:56.002
But if I had the Fours
I wouldn't look it.

13:56.086 --> 13:59.172
Ah. Yes. Yes, you would.
It's gonna be okay.

13:59.256 --> 14:02.133
Pristine upper mesh. Taut laces.

14:02.217 --> 14:03.843
Mmm. [smacks lips]

14:03.927 --> 14:05.762
- Nutty.
- Nasty.

14:05.845 --> 14:06.763
250.

14:06.846 --> 14:08.848
- Come on.
- 250? How dare you.

14:08.932 --> 14:10.559
- [grunts]
- The disrespect.

14:10.642 --> 14:12.936
Come on, Will.
I can do installments.

14:13.019 --> 14:15.939
Yeah, yeah, that's great, Daryl,
but my landlord can't.

14:16.022 --> 14:17.899
[exhales] Okay.

14:17.983 --> 14:19.901
I can't watch this.

14:19.985 --> 14:22.070
So, 400?

14:22.612 --> 14:24.030
- 240.
- I-It's going down?

14:24.114 --> 14:25.407
- 230.
- Dang, stop!

14:25.490 --> 14:26.616
- Please, please!
- [phone chimes]

14:26.700 --> 14:27.826
- Yo!
- [gasps] No way!

14:27.909 --> 14:29.369
Y'all are not
gonna believe this.

14:29.452 --> 14:30.870
Mane is at the Cage,

14:30.954 --> 14:33.873
and he's taking on
all challengers.

14:35.750 --> 14:39.963
So, we, uh, doing this or what?

14:40.046 --> 14:41.381
[sighs] Okay, fine.

14:41.965 --> 14:43.008
All right. Let's dip.

14:43.091 --> 14:45.302
["Hooligang" playing]

14:47.512 --> 14:48.888
[both grunting]

14:50.640 --> 14:52.058
[whinnies]

14:52.142 --> 14:54.144
- [groans]
- Whoo!

14:55.520 --> 14:56.438
Who's got next?

14:56.521 --> 14:58.648
♪ <i>No, nobody can do it like me </i>♪

14:58.732 --> 15:00.025
♪ <i>Zoo Pals plate</i>
<i>With the Kid Cuisine </i>♪

15:00.108 --> 15:01.234
Now watch this.

15:01.901 --> 15:03.028
Give me that.

15:03.111 --> 15:05.071
♪ <i>360s in my green machine </i>♪

15:05.155 --> 15:05.989
Garbage.

15:07.157 --> 15:10.076
I said, who's got next?

15:10.160 --> 15:12.621
I can't hear nothing.
Where y'all at?

15:13.455 --> 15:15.415
Who got next?

15:15.498 --> 15:16.708
[Grizz] Hey, yo. Check ball.

15:17.584 --> 15:18.752
Yeah!

15:18.835 --> 15:20.378
Get him, Grizz!

15:20.462 --> 15:23.131
Got a piece of flaming garbage
over here.

15:24.549 --> 15:26.009
Touch me. Touch me.

15:28.803 --> 15:29.763
[exclaims]

15:29.846 --> 15:31.097
[music ends]

15:31.181 --> 15:32.891
[groans, distorted]

15:34.309 --> 15:36.436
[chuckles] Yeah!

15:36.519 --> 15:38.188
Get lost, Mane, you're a bum.

15:38.271 --> 15:41.650
Seriously? You mean to tell me
this is the best Vineland's got?

15:41.733 --> 15:43.943
I thought the Cage
is where roarball was born.

15:44.027 --> 15:44.861
[whinnies]

15:44.944 --> 15:49.574
I guess this town's only as weak
as its greatest player.

15:49.658 --> 15:51.242
[scoffs] Hey, where she at?

15:51.326 --> 15:55.997
If Jett's nowhere to be found,
then somebody gotta answer me.

15:56.081 --> 15:58.041
- Who's got next?
- [Will] I got next.

15:58.124 --> 15:59.334
Who said that?

15:59.417 --> 16:00.502
[Will] Hey!

16:00.585 --> 16:03.797
Nobody talks about Jett
and Vineland like that.

16:03.880 --> 16:06.591
Excuse me. Pardon.
Hey, move out the way.

16:06.675 --> 16:08.468
- I got next.
- [crowd gasping]

16:08.551 --> 16:09.761
Check up.

16:09.844 --> 16:11.471
Wait, wait, a goat?

16:11.554 --> 16:12.931
[laughing]

16:13.014 --> 16:14.432
[all laughing]

16:14.516 --> 16:15.850
Thank you for the laugh,
little dude,

16:15.934 --> 16:17.519
but, uh, why don't you just
run on back

16:17.602 --> 16:19.229
to the kiddie pool or something.

16:19.312 --> 16:20.438
Get you an ice cream.

16:20.522 --> 16:22.565
But, seriously, any takers?

16:23.191 --> 16:24.693
[Will]
Even if I put money on it?

16:24.776 --> 16:26.486
First the shoes,
now your rent money?

16:26.569 --> 16:28.488
Yes, Will. Commit.

16:28.571 --> 16:30.156
[crowd member 1] Oh, Mane,
what are you gonna do now?

16:30.240 --> 16:31.950
[crowd member 2] Where's all
the big talk now, Mane?

16:32.033 --> 16:33.535
[crowd member 3]
Let's go, Vineland!

16:33.618 --> 16:38.498
Oh. So this is all
the great Vineland has to offer?

16:38.581 --> 16:42.001
A goat and some spare change?
[chuckles]

16:42.085 --> 16:43.211
But you know what?

16:43.294 --> 16:46.005
Mane doesn't duck smoke
so check up.

16:46.089 --> 16:48.258
- Let's do it.
- [camera shutters clicking]

16:48.341 --> 16:50.385
Everything counts as one.

16:50.885 --> 16:51.928
First to three.

16:52.721 --> 16:53.638
Your ball.

16:55.807 --> 16:57.767
- [whinnies, snorts]
- [crowd gasping]

16:59.686 --> 17:01.187
[both chuckling]

17:01.271 --> 17:03.106
- Oh, snap!
- [Will] That's one.

17:03.732 --> 17:04.983
I'd fight a big for that.

17:05.066 --> 17:06.985
- [upbeat music playing]
- [grunts]

17:07.068 --> 17:09.904
Oh. So you do know how to pass.

17:09.988 --> 17:11.406
You gonna guard me
from all the way out there?

17:11.489 --> 17:13.366
[snorts]

17:13.450 --> 17:14.784
Let's go.

17:15.285 --> 17:16.202
Come on.

17:17.912 --> 17:19.164
[both grunting]

17:19.247 --> 17:21.082
[Mane]
When I get that ball, it's over.

17:23.293 --> 17:25.670
Whoa! [whinnies, distorted]

17:26.421 --> 17:27.756
[crowd clamoring]

17:29.466 --> 17:30.842
[laughing]

17:31.760 --> 17:33.636
You got owned by a goat!

17:34.220 --> 17:36.097
- Oh, shoot!
- Hey!

17:36.181 --> 17:37.474
This goat out here!

17:39.851 --> 17:41.936
This dude's eating beans!

17:42.020 --> 17:43.062
[both chuckling]

17:43.146 --> 17:44.397
- [cheering]
- [grunts]

17:44.481 --> 17:46.065
[snorts, grunts]

17:46.149 --> 17:48.193
[camera shutters clicking]

17:48.276 --> 17:50.236
All right. Let's get serious.

17:50.320 --> 17:53.031
Looks like you're gonna make me
take my chains off.

17:53.114 --> 17:55.158
Yeah, man. Take it all off.

17:55.241 --> 17:56.242
- [groans]
- [chuckles]

17:56.326 --> 17:58.119
Oh, okay. I see.

17:58.203 --> 18:00.455
You're an outside shooter, huh?

18:01.247 --> 18:02.415
Now get past me.

18:04.292 --> 18:05.627
Oh. [chuckles]

18:06.586 --> 18:07.921
Now we playing for real.

18:08.004 --> 18:09.547
This is how it feel
in the league.

18:10.173 --> 18:11.132
This is my house.

18:13.092 --> 18:14.886
[chuckles]

18:16.638 --> 18:18.056
You're mine now.

18:18.139 --> 18:19.140
[chuckling]

18:21.434 --> 18:22.769
Boom!

18:22.852 --> 18:25.104
[chuckles, exclaims]

18:25.188 --> 18:26.397
Boom shakalaka!

18:26.481 --> 18:27.774
[groans]

18:28.733 --> 18:29.943
Ooh.

18:30.026 --> 18:31.027
[groans]

18:39.077 --> 18:40.620
Fool, I wasn't helping you up.

18:41.538 --> 18:43.790
- I just wanted my cash.
- [groans]

18:43.873 --> 18:45.166
Thanks.

18:45.250 --> 18:46.960
[crowd clamoring]

18:47.043 --> 18:50.213
- Hey! We got goat money.
- [all cheering]

18:50.296 --> 18:51.422
That wasn't bad.

18:51.464 --> 18:54.676
Everyone didn't have
their phones out for that long.

18:54.759 --> 18:55.844
Right, Daryl?

18:55.927 --> 18:57.887
Yes, they did.

19:04.310 --> 19:06.312
[suspenseful music playing]

19:13.987 --> 19:15.613
[sighs] Come on. Come on.

19:19.617 --> 19:22.704
[both screaming]

19:23.288 --> 19:25.206
[grunts, gasps]

19:25.832 --> 19:26.833
What?

19:30.420 --> 19:31.546
I respect that.

19:31.629 --> 19:32.839
Hey, Will.

19:32.922 --> 19:35.884
Will, uh, I'm really sorry
about my dad.

19:35.967 --> 19:39.637
But I want you to know
I believe in you.

19:39.721 --> 19:40.930
Oh! Oh!

19:41.014 --> 19:43.141
And I made you
a sandwich. Catch!

19:43.224 --> 19:44.934
[majestic music plays, stops]

19:47.478 --> 19:49.439
Oops. Airball.

19:49.522 --> 19:51.232
Sorry about that. [sighs]

19:52.066 --> 19:53.693
[sighs]
Don't even worry about it.

19:53.776 --> 19:55.194
[Theo] I'll still see you
at the Greenhouse

19:55.278 --> 19:56.946
when you're playing for
the Thorns!

19:57.030 --> 19:58.656
- Thanks, Theo.
- Good luck!

20:00.909 --> 20:04.621
Yo, I told you
that video was crazy.

20:04.704 --> 20:06.122
Yeah, that dude was guzzling.

20:06.205 --> 20:08.541
- Yo! What's up, my mammal?
- Hey.

20:08.625 --> 20:10.209
- Oh, hey.
- [Hannah] There he is.

20:10.293 --> 20:13.004
Thanks for letting me crash
at your place.

20:13.087 --> 20:15.715
[Daryl] You brought your stuff?
Hey, throw it on the pile.

20:15.798 --> 20:17.050
Still haven't cleaned.

20:17.133 --> 20:19.093
Okay, just pick a pile.
They're all filthy.

20:19.177 --> 20:20.887
Now quit your yapping
and come check out

20:20.970 --> 20:22.388
what I've been cooking up.

20:24.098 --> 20:26.976
[video game music playing]

20:27.060 --> 20:29.604
[Daryl, Hannah chuckling]

20:30.855 --> 20:34.359
[chuckling continues]

20:37.946 --> 20:38.988
[automated voice] <i>Will wins!</i>

20:39.072 --> 20:40.406
Oh, you like that?

20:40.490 --> 20:42.492
Come on, this is gonna go viral.

20:42.575 --> 20:44.077
You broke his ankles.

20:44.160 --> 20:45.662
Yeah, and he broke my horn.

20:45.745 --> 20:47.080
Ugh. Will, look,

20:47.163 --> 20:49.916
you wanted footage
of you playing against bigs.

20:49.999 --> 20:51.125
And you just went up against

20:51.209 --> 20:53.544
the biggest,
baddest in all of roarball.

20:53.628 --> 20:55.713
- Yep, yep. Facts.
- You did that, Will.

20:55.797 --> 20:58.299
- [sighs]
- Okay.

20:58.383 --> 21:00.343
Well, I'm just gonna
make this one live

21:00.426 --> 21:02.470
'cause I think Daryl
just farted. Ugh.

21:02.553 --> 21:03.680
I'll see you both later.

21:03.763 --> 21:05.807
- I got a date. Need to shave.
- [both] Ooh!

21:05.890 --> 21:07.141
With who?

21:07.225 --> 21:09.686
Oh, I didn't tell you?
Your mom. [chuckling]

21:09.769 --> 21:11.187
Oh, shoot.

21:11.270 --> 21:12.355
Yeah, she got you, bro.

21:12.438 --> 21:15.149
Okay, okay. Wasn't even funny.

21:15.233 --> 21:18.403
Hey, bro.
Wanna play some Roar 2K?

21:18.486 --> 21:19.737
Nah, think I'm good.

21:19.821 --> 21:20.989
Should probably
call it a night, you know?

21:21.072 --> 21:23.074
No, sure thing.
Yeah, make yourself comfortable.

21:23.616 --> 21:25.159
I'm gonna get on these sticks.

21:29.247 --> 21:30.832
[clears throat] Hello!

21:30.915 --> 21:33.209
[screaming]

21:33.292 --> 21:34.544
Okay.

21:34.627 --> 21:36.295
[groans]

21:36.379 --> 21:38.297
Ugh. [sighs]

21:40.133 --> 21:42.385
[train rumbling]

21:46.180 --> 21:47.682
[horn blaring]

21:50.601 --> 21:52.812
[upbeat music playing]

21:59.777 --> 22:01.029
It's him, look.

22:01.696 --> 22:03.781
Look, it's totally him!

22:03.865 --> 22:05.867
[all cheering]

22:06.909 --> 22:08.578
Hey! What's up, buddy?

22:09.912 --> 22:10.913
Hey, Will.

22:10.997 --> 22:13.249
- Hey, Will.
- Hi, anonymous animal.

22:13.332 --> 22:15.043
Look, Mom. It's Will.

22:15.126 --> 22:17.587
- I'm sorry.
- That's okay. It's okay.

22:22.759 --> 22:26.137
Yo, who is the clown
that parked like that outside?

22:26.220 --> 22:27.055
[music ends]

22:27.805 --> 22:28.931
Everybody good?

22:29.015 --> 22:30.892
- [clears throat]
- [trumpets]

22:30.975 --> 22:32.143
Why are y'all not blinking?

22:32.226 --> 22:35.188
That's me, sweetheart.
I'm the clown.

22:35.271 --> 22:37.023
[stammers]
You're Florence Everson!

22:37.106 --> 22:38.483
You're the owner of the Thorns!

22:38.566 --> 22:41.903
You can ignore
all the voicemails, Mr. Harris.

22:41.986 --> 22:44.322
It looks like
I found you myself.

22:44.405 --> 22:46.157
She's been waiting for you.

22:46.240 --> 22:48.159
Without ordering anything.

22:48.659 --> 22:49.702
Sit.

22:49.786 --> 22:52.330
You had quite the game
yesterday.

22:52.413 --> 22:54.040
You broke Mane's ankles so hard,

22:54.123 --> 22:56.084
I thought they were gonna
have to put him down!

22:56.167 --> 22:59.629
And the Internet just loved it.
[chuckles]

22:59.712 --> 23:01.798
- They love you.
- [clicks]

23:01.881 --> 23:04.050
Yo! That's crazy! [chuckles]

23:04.133 --> 23:05.927
Oh, it gets crazier.

23:06.010 --> 23:09.430
Will, maybe you haven't noticed,
but the team is awful.

23:09.514 --> 23:10.515
Oh, no. We trash.

23:10.598 --> 23:12.850
We have the league's best player

23:12.934 --> 23:15.478
and no path
to the Claw, again...

23:15.561 --> 23:16.979
Small to small,

23:17.063 --> 23:19.440
I believe you are exactly

23:19.524 --> 23:22.902
what Jett and this team
needs right now.

23:22.985 --> 23:24.403
Goat, sure.

23:24.487 --> 23:28.449
But I think you might be
a two-horned unicorn.

23:28.533 --> 23:30.159
- Really?
- [chuckles] Yeah.

23:30.243 --> 23:33.496
- I'd like to make you an offer.
- [clicks]

23:33.579 --> 23:34.997
We need a sixth player

23:35.081 --> 23:37.708
to join the Thorns
for the back half of the season.

23:37.792 --> 23:39.502
[gasps] Oh, my gosh.

23:39.585 --> 23:42.004
[stammers] Is it really--
Is it finally happening?

23:42.088 --> 23:44.632
I just need you to sign here,
some initials here,

23:44.715 --> 23:46.467
and you're officially a Thorn.

23:46.551 --> 23:48.803
And, uh, Jett.
She signed off on this?

23:48.886 --> 23:51.764
In many ways,
it was her idea. Yeah.

23:51.848 --> 23:53.266
So what's it gonna be?

23:53.349 --> 23:57.395
Play for Vineland, or stay here
and bus my table?

23:57.478 --> 24:00.106
Pen. Pen! Pen.
Someone give me a pen!

24:00.189 --> 24:01.357
I don't have a-- Ow!

24:02.150 --> 24:03.276
Thank you.

24:04.902 --> 24:07.113
W. H.

24:07.196 --> 24:09.782
Where there's a Will,
there's a way.

24:09.866 --> 24:14.287
Oh, congratulations, sweetie.
We're so proud of you.

24:14.370 --> 24:16.622
[all chanting]
Will! Will! Will! Will! Will!

24:18.207 --> 24:19.458
I cannot believe it!

24:19.542 --> 24:21.669
I'm gonna be a Vineland Thorn!

24:21.752 --> 24:23.754
- Breaking news!
- You're not gonna believe it!

24:23.838 --> 24:25.715
- Will, it went viral!
- It certainly did.

24:25.798 --> 24:27.383
I'm so excited, Will.

24:27.466 --> 24:29.719
- Who's the fancy pig?
- [chuckles]

24:29.802 --> 24:31.888
I hate this town.

24:33.639 --> 24:35.933
- [alarm beeping]
- [Jett grunting]

24:41.397 --> 24:42.773
[groans]

24:43.733 --> 24:45.067
[grunts]

24:48.946 --> 24:51.282
- [grunts]
- [spine cracking]

24:51.365 --> 24:53.201
Oh. It hurts. It hurts.

24:53.284 --> 24:55.244
- [spine cracking]
- [sighs]

24:56.913 --> 24:58.623
[licking]

24:59.165 --> 25:01.083
<i>Welcome to the </i>Roar Roundup<i>.</i>

25:01.167 --> 25:03.085
<i>I'm two-time champion, Chuck,</i>

25:03.169 --> 25:06.088
<i>alongside my cohost,</i>
<i>itty-bitty-bitey-buddy,</i>

25:06.172 --> 25:07.506
<i>- Rusty.</i>
- <i>Rusty!</i> [chuckles]

25:07.590 --> 25:09.967
<i>I can't wait till they put you</i>
<i>out to pasture, Chuck.</i>

25:10.051 --> 25:11.510
[chuckles] <i>That's good.</i>

25:11.594 --> 25:14.513
<i>Well, but back to the question</i>
<i>we ask every season.</i>

25:14.597 --> 25:16.682
[Rusty] <i>Can you be the GOAT</i>
<i>without winning a championship?</i>

25:16.766 --> 25:17.850
- Uh, yeah.
- [spine clicks]

25:17.934 --> 25:19.435
- [Chuck] <i>Claws make careers.</i>
- What is that?

25:19.518 --> 25:20.645
- [Rusty] <i>You don't say!</i>
- Nuh-uh.

25:20.728 --> 25:22.813
<i>I feel for Fillmore. She's</i>
<i>always been a great player,</i>

25:22.897 --> 25:25.024
<i>but Father Time</i>
<i>catches up with everyone.</i>

25:25.107 --> 25:27.443
Without me, they wouldn't
have anything to talk about.

25:27.526 --> 25:29.153
[Chuck] <i>All stats, no Claws.</i>

25:29.237 --> 25:30.905
<i>But you can't</i>
<i>put all the blame on her.</i>

25:30.988 --> 25:32.073
<i>Anyone who's watched this team</i>

25:32.156 --> 25:34.325
<i>and thinks Jett's the biggest</i>
<i>problem is blind as a--</i>

25:34.408 --> 25:37.787
<i>Blind as a what, Chuck? Say it.</i>
<i>Blind as a what?</i>

25:37.870 --> 25:41.332
I am the all-time leading scorer
in Roar history.

25:41.415 --> 25:42.416
[Rusty] <i>Speaking of the Thorns,</i>

25:42.500 --> 25:44.919
<i>we've got some</i>
<i>breaking news, Chuck!</i>

25:45.002 --> 25:46.921
<i>The Vineland Thorns have finally</i>
<i>signed a sixth player.</i>

25:47.004 --> 25:48.798
<i>Looks like they're finally</i>
<i>getting Jett some help.</i>

25:48.881 --> 25:50.091
Yes! A crocodile?

25:50.174 --> 25:51.342
No, no, no, no.
Bigger. A gorilla?

25:51.425 --> 25:53.177
[Rusty] <i>We go now to</i>
<i>owner Florence Everson...</i>

25:53.261 --> 25:54.262
That's what I'm talking about.

25:54.345 --> 25:55.596
<i>...with an exclusive interview.</i>

25:55.680 --> 25:58.266
<i>We signed</i>
<i>roarball's first small.</i>

25:58.349 --> 25:59.767
A small what?

25:59.850 --> 26:01.477
<i>We got a little...</i>

26:01.560 --> 26:02.520
A little, uh, what?

26:02.603 --> 26:04.272
- <i>...teeny...</i>
- A what now?

26:04.355 --> 26:05.731
- <i>...tiny...</i>
- Come again.

26:05.815 --> 26:07.358
- <i>...goat.</i>
- [goat bleats]

26:07.858 --> 26:09.402
A goat?

26:09.485 --> 26:11.153
[growling]

26:12.488 --> 26:13.447
[engine revs]

26:25.001 --> 26:27.253
Oh, not again.

26:27.336 --> 26:29.171
- Florence Marjorie Everson!
- [glass smashes]

26:29.255 --> 26:33.050
You're signing a goat?
Have you lost your mind?

26:33.134 --> 26:35.344
Okay. Excuse me.

26:35.428 --> 26:38.431
You're the one who asked for
a team who could win the Claw

26:38.514 --> 26:41.058
and you didn't care how.
Remember?

26:41.142 --> 26:43.227
Well, I care about this.

26:43.311 --> 26:45.021
I can't play with a goat.

26:45.104 --> 26:46.981
He's an embarrassment
to the team.

26:47.064 --> 26:49.150
He's an embarrassment
to the city. He's a--

26:49.233 --> 26:50.651
Uh... He's sitting right there.

26:52.111 --> 26:53.738
Hey!

26:55.489 --> 26:56.949
You gotta be kidding me.

26:57.033 --> 26:59.076
I couldn't even see him
in the chair, Flo.

26:59.160 --> 27:00.661
How am I supposed to
see him on the court?

27:00.745 --> 27:02.997
I'll be the goat
in the Thorns jersey.

27:03.080 --> 27:04.081
You feel me?

27:04.165 --> 27:05.583
Uh-huh.

27:05.666 --> 27:07.376
Look away, Flo.
I'm just gonna eat him.

27:07.501 --> 27:09.920
Yeah, I'm gonna eat him
with a side of ranch dressing,

27:10.004 --> 27:12.506
and we're gonna act
like none of this happened.

27:12.590 --> 27:14.633
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
I do not taste good.

27:14.717 --> 27:16.052
I-I thought you said she knew.

27:16.135 --> 27:18.220
It's my job to bend
the truth, Will. Come on.

27:18.304 --> 27:19.430
[meows, growls]

27:19.513 --> 27:23.017
It's also my job
to play the long game.

27:23.100 --> 27:24.477
This is generating
more attention

27:24.560 --> 27:26.604
than we have had in years.

27:26.687 --> 27:28.939
You don't want him on the court,
that's your call.

27:29.023 --> 27:32.026
- But he stays on the roster.
- [Jett growling]

27:32.109 --> 27:34.070
Oh, you must have
lost your mind.

27:34.153 --> 27:36.739
- Put your paw down.
- [sighs]

27:36.822 --> 27:38.616
You should be elated.

27:38.699 --> 27:40.618
The stars have aligned perfectly

27:40.701 --> 27:43.579
because the press is
dying to meet Will.

27:43.662 --> 27:45.373
Will, down. Get down.

27:45.456 --> 27:46.457
[Will] Oh, okay.

27:46.540 --> 27:47.750
And I want you to introduce him.

27:47.833 --> 27:49.877
- No. Not happening.
- Yes, you are.

27:49.960 --> 27:52.546
They're actually waiting for you
right downstairs.

27:52.630 --> 27:54.840
So keep them tails up high, yes?

27:54.924 --> 27:58.010
Big smiles!
Love you both! Now get out!

28:00.930 --> 28:02.473
- Jett, hey.
- [sighs]

28:02.556 --> 28:05.851
I just wanted you to know,
this is my dream come true.

28:05.935 --> 28:09.063
I mean, to play with you, like,
my favorite player of all time.

28:09.605 --> 28:11.357
I know I'm not
what you expected,

28:11.440 --> 28:14.276
but I've spent my whole life
training for this moment.

28:14.360 --> 28:15.945
And if you just give me a sho--

28:16.028 --> 28:19.532
Look, kid.
I saw your little viral video.

28:19.615 --> 28:21.700
Mane baked you
like a birthday cake.

28:21.784 --> 28:23.119
Yeah, yeah, no. I'm gonna enjoy

28:23.202 --> 28:25.121
watching the piranhas
eat you alive.

28:25.204 --> 28:28.833
- Jett! Over here! Jett!
- Hey, Jett! Over here!

28:28.916 --> 28:30.251
- Will! Will!
- Will, over here!

28:30.334 --> 28:31.752
- Will!
- Will, over here!

28:31.836 --> 28:34.213
- Will, over here!
- Will, Will, Will!

28:37.383 --> 28:39.135
- [Will grunts]
- [chair squeaking]

28:40.010 --> 28:43.180
- [chair squeaking]
- [scoffs]

28:43.264 --> 28:44.557
[chair rattles, clicks]

28:46.851 --> 28:49.854
[chair squeaking]

28:50.855 --> 28:52.940
Let's get started.
Hardest questions first.

28:53.023 --> 28:54.984
Do you think going viral
in a playground entitles you

28:55.067 --> 28:56.068
to play professional roarball?

28:56.152 --> 28:57.528
Do you worry
you'll let other smalls down?

28:57.611 --> 28:59.155
Aren't you just
a shameless publicity stunt

28:59.238 --> 29:01.073
to distract from another
Thorns losing season?

29:01.157 --> 29:02.158
[reporter 1]
Are you actually a goat?

29:02.241 --> 29:03.784
[reporter 2]
Don't you just kinda suck?

29:03.868 --> 29:05.870
I... Sorry. Can--
Can you repeat the question?

29:05.953 --> 29:08.372
Hey, hey. One at a time, y'all.

29:08.456 --> 29:10.958
This boy is not even
media trained, okay?

29:11.041 --> 29:13.252
So, Will. How does it feel
to be the first small ever

29:13.335 --> 29:15.004
to sign a professional
roarball contract?

29:15.087 --> 29:18.674
Uh, to be honest with you,
it's all kinda surreal.

29:18.757 --> 29:20.384
I mean, last night
I was fighting off roaches

29:20.468 --> 29:21.802
- at my best friend's crib...
- [crowd gasps]

29:21.886 --> 29:24.346
...and now
I'm playing for the Thorns.

29:24.430 --> 29:26.265
[groans]
You shouldn't have said that.

29:26.348 --> 29:27.808
Will, we are getting word
that the roach community

29:27.892 --> 29:29.560
was pretty offended
by your last comment.

29:29.643 --> 29:30.936
Would you care to
issue an apology?

29:31.020 --> 29:33.189
Oh, gosh. No, no, no, no.
That's not what I meant.

29:33.272 --> 29:35.191
- [stammers] I love roaches.
- Lies.

29:35.274 --> 29:36.567
Can we, uh,
move on to the next question?

29:36.650 --> 29:37.485
Up here.

29:37.568 --> 29:40.112
So, Will, you're not at all
concerned about being hurt?

29:40.196 --> 29:42.198
Roarball takes its toll on
the toughest of bigs.

29:42.281 --> 29:43.282
I imagine for a small,

29:43.365 --> 29:45.075
- it could be fatal.
- [crowd gasping]

29:45.159 --> 29:48.204
- Uh, well...
- No, no. Will knows the risks.

29:48.287 --> 29:50.581
Could he be clobbered? Possibly.

29:50.664 --> 29:52.208
Crushed? Perhaps.

29:52.291 --> 29:54.168
- Killed? Probably.
- [crowd gasps]

29:54.251 --> 29:56.670
But that's how much
he loves the game.

29:56.754 --> 29:58.380
- He'd die for it.
- [gulps]

29:59.006 --> 30:01.300
- Right, Will?
- [chuckles] Right.

30:01.383 --> 30:02.468
What about Mane?

30:02.551 --> 30:04.345
Are you worried about a rematch
down the line?

30:04.428 --> 30:05.429
No. No way.

30:05.513 --> 30:07.014
We call this dude
the horse whisperer,

30:07.097 --> 30:09.725
'cause he broke
that bronco's back, okay?

30:09.808 --> 30:11.352
You know what
he was telling me earlier?

30:11.435 --> 30:12.978
He's got a nickname for Mane.

30:13.062 --> 30:15.856
- He calls him "My Little Pony."
- [crowd laughing]

30:15.940 --> 30:17.441
- Don't you?
- No, I didn't say that.

30:17.525 --> 30:18.692
- You do.
- I did not say that.

30:18.776 --> 30:22.279
And he also said that Mane
definitely ain't the GOAT,

30:22.780 --> 30:25.115
<i>and his hair is wack, too,</i>
<i>which I also agree with.</i>

30:25.199 --> 30:26.325
Oh, he's dead.

30:26.408 --> 30:28.536
- Why are you doing this to me?
- [reporter 3] Last question.

30:28.619 --> 30:30.120
Uh, this one's for Jett.
You're in year fifteen.

30:30.204 --> 30:32.248
The team's bringing on a goat
to solve its problems.

30:32.331 --> 30:34.542
Do you ever wonder
if it's time to hang it up?

30:34.625 --> 30:36.835
[chuckles] I'm not hanging up
anything, okay?

30:36.919 --> 30:38.003
I feel great right now,

30:38.087 --> 30:39.797
playing some of
the best ball of my career.

30:39.880 --> 30:41.382
And please,
I've played with every mutt

30:41.465 --> 30:42.967
this league has to offer.

30:43.050 --> 30:45.928
My only concern
is going out there

30:46.011 --> 30:48.806
and doing what I gotta do
to win the Claw,

30:48.889 --> 30:52.476
and nothing, and I mean nothing,
is gonna get in the way of that.

30:52.560 --> 30:54.603
Thank you.
Bagels on the third floor.

30:54.687 --> 30:55.729
Jett, over here!

30:55.813 --> 30:57.523
Yeah. Uh, cool.

30:57.606 --> 30:58.440
[reporter 4] Will!

30:58.524 --> 30:59.692
[reporter 5]
Do you have any comment?

30:59.775 --> 31:01.777
I can-- Okay, thank you.

31:02.278 --> 31:03.529
Bye.

31:05.281 --> 31:06.699
[interviewer]
Coach Dennis, how do you plan

31:06.782 --> 31:09.076
on utilizing the goat
in the rotation?

31:09.159 --> 31:11.495
That's a great question. Well--

31:11.579 --> 31:13.581
[Jett] Dennis, he's all yours.

31:13.664 --> 31:15.040
[Dennis]
Hey, Jett, you got a second?

31:15.124 --> 31:17.668
I just wanted to
go over these new plays.

31:17.751 --> 31:18.836
[clears throat, chuckles]

31:18.919 --> 31:21.714
You heard me.
Uh, we'll do it later. [laughs]

31:21.797 --> 31:23.299
How you doing, kid?
Dennis Cooper.

31:23.382 --> 31:24.216
Pleased to meet you.

31:24.300 --> 31:27.636
Oh, I know you, Coach Dennis.
It's an honor.

31:27.720 --> 31:29.513
Coach is a strong word.

31:29.597 --> 31:32.558
I'm more of
an underpaid clipboard stand.

31:32.641 --> 31:33.684
[chuckles] Whee!

31:33.767 --> 31:34.852
But I keep trying.

31:34.935 --> 31:36.729
Uh, let's get you suited up
for the game.

31:36.812 --> 31:37.730
I'm ready to play.

31:37.813 --> 31:40.274
Play? [chuckles]
I... That's cute. No.

31:40.357 --> 31:41.233
- What?
- Nothing.

31:42.109 --> 31:43.819
And here we are.

31:43.902 --> 31:45.362
[majestic music playing]

31:45.446 --> 31:48.407
No way. The Thorns locker room?

31:48.991 --> 31:51.243
[squeals] Yes!

31:51.327 --> 31:53.746
Get dressed
and come meet the team.

31:53.829 --> 31:56.665
[giggles] Yes, yes, yes, yes!

31:56.749 --> 31:58.500
This is crazy!

31:58.584 --> 31:59.585
[gasps]

32:01.253 --> 32:06.425
Yo! My name. On a Thorns jersey.

32:08.052 --> 32:11.639
Oh, wait. Fillmore 13's?

32:11.722 --> 32:13.140
[giggles]

32:19.813 --> 32:20.814
[exhales]

32:21.732 --> 32:22.858
Not bad.

32:25.861 --> 32:26.904
Right?

32:30.407 --> 32:31.659
[Chuck] <i>It's game night.</i>

32:31.742 --> 32:35.954
<i>Welcome back to Regionally</i>
<i>Organized Animal Roarball.</i>

32:36.038 --> 32:38.290
<i>The sport with</i>
<i>the wildest courts.</i>

32:38.374 --> 32:39.583
[Rusty] <i>Stalactites.</i>

32:39.667 --> 32:40.876
<i>Sandstorms.</i>

32:40.959 --> 32:41.794
<i>Cliffs.</i>

32:41.877 --> 32:42.753
<i>Ice.</i>

32:42.836 --> 32:45.005
<i>Fire. And vines!</i>

32:45.089 --> 32:46.548
[Chuck] <i>Tonight,</i>
<i>we're at the Greenhouse,</i>

32:46.632 --> 32:48.384
<i>and the stadium is rocking</i>

32:48.467 --> 32:50.386
<i>for the first</i>
<i>of three straight home games.</i>

32:50.469 --> 32:53.389
<i>And no surprise,</i>
<i>the smalls have shown up big</i>

32:53.472 --> 32:55.516
<i>- for Vineland's newest Thorn.</i>
- [yelps]

32:55.599 --> 32:56.809
♪ <i>Y'all ready for this? </i>♪

32:58.936 --> 33:02.106
[Rusty chuckling]
<i>The Canoodle Cam is on patrol!</i>

33:02.189 --> 33:04.775
[Chuck giggles]
<i>Somebunny's in love!</i>

33:04.858 --> 33:06.568
<i>Looks like they're necking!</i>

33:06.652 --> 33:10.072
[Rusty] <i>"Polly want a cracker?"</i>
<i>Am I right, up-Chuck?</i> [laughs]

33:14.660 --> 33:15.869
Oh, you caught it!

33:15.953 --> 33:17.079
[chuckling]

33:17.162 --> 33:19.081
I'm a genius.

33:19.164 --> 33:21.750
Okay, Olivia. Clear your mind.

33:21.834 --> 33:23.168
I am in control.

33:23.252 --> 33:25.838
I know who I am.
I am good enough.

33:25.921 --> 33:28.215
I do not care about
the opinions of others.

33:28.298 --> 33:30.342
I do not care what
they're saying about me online,

33:30.426 --> 33:33.429
right now, across multiple
platforms which I could check,

33:33.512 --> 33:34.805
just to see what they're saying.

33:34.888 --> 33:37.474
Phone! Phone.
Does anyone have a phone?

33:37.558 --> 33:38.934
You're not even in uniform!

33:39.017 --> 33:41.228
Ha! It's tear-away.

33:41.311 --> 33:43.230
- Oh, Lenny.
- We're gonna get you!

33:43.313 --> 33:45.566
- [groaning]
- Daddy's a yeti!

33:45.649 --> 33:50.404
[chuckles] Listen. I celebrate
your creativity with the foam,

33:50.487 --> 33:54.950
but it's not okay to shoot Daddy
in the face, okay? Great.

33:55.033 --> 33:55.993
[giggling]

33:56.076 --> 33:57.161
Cute kids.

33:57.244 --> 33:58.579
Yeah, I know. Right?

33:58.662 --> 34:01.665
Don't look now, but there's
a baby goat walking towards us

34:01.749 --> 34:04.126
with a weird smile on his face.

34:04.209 --> 34:05.711
Uh, I'm Will Harris.

34:05.794 --> 34:09.173
Ready to help the team win
however I can.

34:09.256 --> 34:12.885
- Oh, look, a pre-game snack.
- [gasps]

34:12.968 --> 34:15.637
Let me just unhinge my jaw.

34:15.721 --> 34:17.556
Please, please! No!
Don't eat me! Don't eat me!

34:17.639 --> 34:19.933
- It's the viral kid!
- He's sick?

34:20.017 --> 34:21.977
No, he went viral.

34:22.060 --> 34:26.482
- Weird. I like it. Come. Dance.
- [mysterious music playing]

34:26.565 --> 34:29.193
We're not doing
your little dance, Modo.

34:29.276 --> 34:30.861
[team member] I kinda like it.

34:30.944 --> 34:32.529
[rasping, chuckling]

34:32.613 --> 34:34.490
[muttering]

34:34.573 --> 34:37.201
Uh, what's with the egg?

34:37.284 --> 34:39.077
- [shushing]
- [music stops]

34:39.161 --> 34:43.707
Don't let them control you.
[chuckling, rasps]

34:43.791 --> 34:45.584
[crowd chanting] Roots run deep.

34:46.126 --> 34:47.753
Roots run deep.

34:47.836 --> 34:49.338
- Roots run deep.
- [rumbling]

34:49.421 --> 34:52.090
It's really loud
in here, right? [groans]

34:52.174 --> 34:55.511
Hey, Jett? Do you think I'll get
some playing time tonight?

34:55.594 --> 34:56.887
[scoffs]

34:56.970 --> 35:00.474
[announcer]
<i>Introducing your newest Thorn.</i>

35:01.183 --> 35:05.145
<i>- Coming in at a hot 5'7"...</i>
- [crowd booing]

35:05.229 --> 35:06.939
<i>...from South Vineland,</i>

35:07.022 --> 35:13.362
<i>the Mane-slayer himself,</i>
<i>Will Harris!</i>

35:13.445 --> 35:15.948
[booing continues]

35:17.199 --> 35:18.951
Where'd he go?
I can't see him. [laughs]

35:19.034 --> 35:20.369
Will history be made tonight,

35:20.452 --> 35:23.372
or will he follow in your
underwhelming footsteps, Chuck?

35:23.455 --> 35:25.833
You suck, Rusty.
And yes, that was a bat joke.

35:25.916 --> 35:27.793
- Yeah! Let's go, Will!
- Yeah, Will!

35:27.876 --> 35:30.420
That's Will, right?
He kind of looks like a gerbil.

35:30.504 --> 35:32.256
Do you think Will's gonna play?

35:32.339 --> 35:34.842
I hope not, or we're gonna watch
that kid die on live TV.

35:34.925 --> 35:35.843
[all] Gerald!

35:38.136 --> 35:39.137
[growls]

35:41.723 --> 35:44.643
- Great! Yes! There it is!
- Let's go, baby! Keep it up!

35:44.726 --> 35:46.478
Hey, Coach, when do you think
I might get in?

35:46.562 --> 35:50.148
- Just study the playbook, kid.
- End his bloodline!

35:50.232 --> 35:51.692
Oh, story time?

35:51.775 --> 35:55.737
Yeah. Bring it in. Once, there
was a play called Eagle 24.

35:55.821 --> 35:57.406
- Oh, I like this one.
- [whistle blows]

35:57.489 --> 35:59.825
Anyone tired? I could sub in.

35:59.908 --> 36:01.118
- I could take a break.
- No.

36:01.869 --> 36:04.872
He's gonna be playing
in the next game. Trust me.

36:06.206 --> 36:07.332
We need a bucket here.

36:07.416 --> 36:10.210
Modo, hang out on the perimeter.
Space the floor.

36:10.294 --> 36:11.962
- Do your thing.
- [Modo rasps]

36:12.045 --> 36:14.756
I always do.

36:15.674 --> 36:16.633
Ball! Ball!

36:16.717 --> 36:18.385
Ball! Ball! Ball! Ball!

36:18.468 --> 36:20.762
Ball! Ball! [grunts]

36:20.846 --> 36:24.141
Hey, I actually noticed that
the moose always drives right,

36:24.224 --> 36:27.227
so if you just
shift the defense a li--

36:27.311 --> 36:29.021
Who wants an acacia leaf break?

36:29.104 --> 36:31.356
- [team member] Ooh, ooh. I do!
- [groans]

36:31.440 --> 36:33.525
- [grunts, chuckles]
- [buzzer sounds]

36:33.609 --> 36:36.904
Tomorrow, history
will be made... [chuckles]

36:36.987 --> 36:38.196
...and I mean it this time.

36:39.781 --> 36:40.991
Shake it off, Archie!

36:41.074 --> 36:43.493
I got water, towels,
emotional support.

36:43.577 --> 36:44.411
I'm covered.

36:44.494 --> 36:47.372
[Rusty] <i>Three tough losses in</i>
<i>a row for the Vineland Thorns.</i>

36:47.456 --> 36:48.999
[Chuck] <i>And now they'll</i>
<i>hit the road with a goat</i>

36:49.082 --> 36:52.044
<i>who's yet to see</i>
<i>a dime of playing time.</i>

36:55.297 --> 36:57.007
- [spine clicks]
- Ouch. Ooh. [sighs]

37:01.303 --> 37:02.304
[exhales]

37:04.181 --> 37:05.474
[wheels squeaking]

37:08.727 --> 37:10.354
No days off, am I right?

37:10.437 --> 37:11.480
No, no, no. Nope.

37:11.563 --> 37:13.315
This is
a private practice session.

37:13.398 --> 37:16.318
Hey, watch this.
From the logo. Nothing but net.

37:17.277 --> 37:18.528
[ball bouncing]

37:18.612 --> 37:20.489
Hmm. Lucky shot.

37:20.572 --> 37:22.282
Hmm. Maybe.

37:22.366 --> 37:23.200
Bank shot.

37:23.825 --> 37:25.994
[chuckling]
Should I play the lottery?

37:26.078 --> 37:26.912
I'm feeling good today.

37:26.995 --> 37:28.747
Why are you here, kid?

37:28.830 --> 37:30.540
I want some playing time.

37:30.624 --> 37:32.250
[chuckles] Not happening.

37:32.334 --> 37:33.377
Let's shoot for it.

37:33.460 --> 37:36.338
Or are you scared
you're gonna lose to a goat?

37:37.756 --> 37:39.549
[chuckles] All right. Bet.

37:39.633 --> 37:42.260
Top of the stands,
hook shot off the glass,

37:42.344 --> 37:43.929
spin around the rim, in.

37:44.012 --> 37:45.847
[upbeat music playing]

37:47.432 --> 37:49.393
Jett from downtown.
[gasps] Did it.

37:53.981 --> 37:55.315
Easy.

37:55.399 --> 37:56.984
[Jett] Through the vines, in.

37:57.067 --> 37:59.403
[blowing] Hot paws over here.

38:00.988 --> 38:02.364
- Yeah, baby!
- [scoffs]

38:02.447 --> 38:03.448
[Will] What else you got?

38:03.532 --> 38:05.200
Off the top,

38:05.283 --> 38:06.535
in.

38:06.618 --> 38:08.161
Ooh. [giggling]

38:10.080 --> 38:10.998
[whistles]

38:11.081 --> 38:12.457
[chuckling] Whoo-hoo!

38:12.541 --> 38:13.959
[Will giggling]

38:14.042 --> 38:15.335
[Jett] Hanging from the lights.

38:16.545 --> 38:17.879
Easy.

38:20.799 --> 38:22.801
[music stops]

38:22.884 --> 38:24.094
Ooh!

38:24.177 --> 38:26.054
You are mine now.

38:27.139 --> 38:28.432
- [music resumes]
- [chuckling]

38:28.515 --> 38:30.976
From the tunnel,
over the backboard,

38:31.059 --> 38:33.311
nothing but net. All right?

38:33.395 --> 38:34.938
If I hit this one,

38:35.022 --> 38:38.358
you have to give me
playing time. Huh?

38:38.442 --> 38:40.235
Okay, yeah. We'll see.

38:41.278 --> 38:43.697
- Pack it up.
- [screams]

38:45.198 --> 38:47.200
Ah. You missed. [chuckles]

38:47.284 --> 38:50.245
[Dennis] Come on, we gotta fly.
Plane leaves in 30.

38:50.328 --> 38:51.621
♪ <i>Crazy </i>♪

38:51.705 --> 38:54.082
♪ <i>Wait till the world's all mine</i>
<i>It's gonna be crazy </i>♪

38:54.166 --> 38:55.625
♪ <i>Crazy </i>♪

38:55.709 --> 38:58.086
♪ <i>Everything I survived</i>
<i>I must be crazy </i>♪

38:58.170 --> 38:59.588
♪ <i>Crazy </i>♪

38:59.671 --> 39:01.673
[panting]

39:01.757 --> 39:03.884
I really had to
hustle back there, but...

39:03.967 --> 39:06.136
Yo! [stammers] What?

39:06.219 --> 39:07.304
We're on a PJ?

39:07.387 --> 39:08.638
- [chuckles]
- [song ends]

39:08.722 --> 39:09.723
[gasps]

39:09.806 --> 39:11.391
What? Oh, sick.

39:11.475 --> 39:14.102
- Are you seeing this? Oh, no.
- [child] You got dunked on!

39:14.186 --> 39:15.979
Are y'all playing Roar 2K?

39:16.063 --> 39:18.648
They've added memes?
I mean, why would they do that?

39:18.732 --> 39:20.108
It's so disrespectful!

39:20.192 --> 39:22.861
Not just to me...
[muffled] ...but to all birds.

39:22.944 --> 39:26.615
Auntie Olivia
is not giving bird. Birds fly.

39:26.698 --> 39:27.908
Are you broken?

39:27.991 --> 39:29.076
Hey, hey, uh,

39:29.159 --> 39:33.330
Auntie Olivia has a condition
called flightless bird syndrome.

39:33.413 --> 39:36.750
Aw. Auntie Olivia can't fly.

39:36.833 --> 39:40.003
- [both] But we can! [chuckling]
- Oh, no! Not the cockpit!

39:40.087 --> 39:41.171
Girls!

39:41.254 --> 39:43.131
[child 1]
We're taking over this plane!

39:43.215 --> 39:45.092
- [child 2] Reporting for duty!
- [Archie] No, don't touch that!

39:45.175 --> 39:46.760
Ah. At least the bags are comfy.

39:46.843 --> 39:49.137
- Hey, Lenny. Is this seat taken?
- Yep.

39:49.221 --> 39:51.389
- By who?
- [Lenny] By me.

39:51.473 --> 39:53.100
- [exhales] Ooh, that's good.
- [squeaking]

39:53.183 --> 39:54.643
Are you really trying to
body-shame me

39:54.726 --> 39:55.977
for needing two seats?

39:56.061 --> 39:57.062
Sorry. My bad.

39:57.145 --> 39:59.064
- Hey, Modo. Is this seat taken?
- [rasping]

39:59.147 --> 40:01.233
Eh. Technically speaking, nah.

40:01.316 --> 40:02.818
[squelching]

40:02.901 --> 40:04.361
[screams]

40:04.444 --> 40:05.529
What the... Ew.

40:05.612 --> 40:07.322
Oh. [chuckling]
That's just my skin.

40:07.405 --> 40:09.825
[yawns] I molted.

40:09.908 --> 40:12.202
[exclaims, chuckles]

40:12.285 --> 40:14.621
Ugh. Okay. There you go.

40:14.704 --> 40:15.872
- [snoring]
- [groans]

40:15.956 --> 40:17.040
Jett!

40:17.124 --> 40:18.125
Hey.

40:18.208 --> 40:20.085
So, you were shooting around
with the kid.

40:20.168 --> 40:21.711
- [Will] Jett!
- He's good, huh?

40:21.795 --> 40:23.755
My mama could make
those shots, okay? [scoffs]

40:23.839 --> 40:25.132
Doesn't mean
he can play. [chuckles]

40:25.215 --> 40:26.466
Hey, Jett!

40:26.550 --> 40:27.717
[grunts, sighs]

40:27.801 --> 40:29.886
- I made it. Huh?
- [snoring continues]

40:29.970 --> 40:32.764
Hey, everyone,
a round of applause.

40:32.848 --> 40:33.890
Will made it.

40:33.974 --> 40:35.684
Oh. Spicy.

40:35.767 --> 40:37.435
Is following me around
being annoying

40:37.519 --> 40:40.105
your full-time job,
or... [sputters]

40:40.188 --> 40:41.982
You-You-You have to open it.

40:42.065 --> 40:44.818
The nuts,
they're inside the can.

40:44.901 --> 40:47.487
Wait. So the can isn't the food?

40:47.571 --> 40:48.864
[groans]

40:48.947 --> 40:50.615
- [chuckles]
- [phone chimes]

40:50.699 --> 40:51.825
Mane dropped a...

40:51.908 --> 40:53.910
[gasps]
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no!

40:53.994 --> 40:57.497
Mane just dropped a diss track
about goat boy!

40:57.581 --> 40:59.374
Oh, Olivia,
put it on the big screen.

40:59.457 --> 41:01.126
- Wait! No, wait.
- You got it, Miss Lady Girl.

41:01.209 --> 41:03.670
- Modo's still sleeping.
- Actually, I'm wide awake.

41:03.753 --> 41:07.132
- I am here for this. Let's go!
- [Will groans]

41:07.215 --> 41:08.842
- Oh, yeah! Let's hear that one.
- Oh, no.

41:08.925 --> 41:09.759
Oh, yes.

41:09.843 --> 41:11.219
[Will] No, please!
No, no, no, no.

41:13.013 --> 41:15.182
[hip-hop music playing]

41:15.265 --> 41:16.641
[Mane] You're not ready.

41:18.101 --> 41:21.396
It's Mane season! [chuckles]

41:21.479 --> 41:22.731
You know what's in my cup!

41:22.814 --> 41:24.816
♪ <i>I know you think</i>
<i>You're all "ba-a-ad" </i>♪

41:24.900 --> 41:27.485
♪ <i>But I'ma have you crying l</i>
<i>Like "ba-a-a" </i>♪

41:27.569 --> 41:29.738
♪ <i>You just goat here, I'm</i>
<i>The Mane Attraction, though </i>♪

41:29.821 --> 41:32.115
♪ <i>I'm the Godfather</i>
<i>Call me Pony Soprano </i>♪

41:32.199 --> 41:34.201
♪ <i>I'ma keep it short</i>
<i>Just like you </i>♪

41:34.284 --> 41:37.037
♪ <i>Next time we on the court</i>
<i>The smoke's on you </i>♪

41:37.120 --> 41:39.206
♪ <i>Act tough, but you're scared</i>
<i>I'm in your nightmares </i>♪

41:39.289 --> 41:40.207
♪ <i>Tonight, when you sleep </i>♪

41:40.290 --> 41:42.334
♪ <i>You'll be crying</i>
<i>Goat tears, goat tears </i>♪

41:42.459 --> 41:45.170
♪ <i>You'll be crying</i>
<i>Goat tears, goat tears </i>♪

41:45.253 --> 41:47.088
♪ <i>You'll be crying</i>
<i>Goat tears, goat tears </i>♪

41:47.172 --> 41:48.173
[song ends]

41:48.256 --> 41:51.259
- [Modo chuckles]
- [Olivia] Oh, that is a banger!

41:51.343 --> 41:53.220
[Lenny] Eh,
the lyrics are kinda mid.

41:56.431 --> 41:58.475
[team members] ♪<i>You'll be crying</i>
<i>Goat tears, goat, goat </i>♪

41:58.558 --> 42:00.101
♪ <i>You'll be crying</i>
<i>Goat tears, goat </i>♪

42:00.185 --> 42:02.687
♪<i>Tasty Goat, you'll be crying</i>
<i>Goat tears, goat </i>♪

42:02.771 --> 42:04.105
[sighs]

42:05.649 --> 42:07.651
[whirring, dings]

42:07.734 --> 42:08.735
[upbeat music playing]

42:08.818 --> 42:10.237
Yo!

42:10.820 --> 42:12.322
It smells so good in here.

42:15.492 --> 42:16.493
[beeps]

42:19.579 --> 42:21.915
This... this is where
I wanna be at.

42:21.998 --> 42:24.751
What is that? I've never...
This could be in a room?

42:25.377 --> 42:27.796
Yeah, baby!
We chilling in a penthouse!

42:27.879 --> 42:29.172
[singsongy]
We chilling in a penthouse.

42:29.256 --> 42:31.591
We chilling in a penthouse.
We chilling in a pent...

42:31.675 --> 42:34.052
- Oh! This is crazy!
- [phone ringing]

42:34.135 --> 42:36.054
<i>Hey! Look who it is!</i>

42:36.137 --> 42:36.972
Hold up, hold up, hold up.

42:37.055 --> 42:38.723
You guys ain't gonna believe
this place.

42:38.807 --> 42:41.476
Yo, bros, bros. We got
a 95-inch TV in the living room.

42:41.559 --> 42:42.394
You see that? Aight.

42:42.477 --> 42:44.062
TV on the toilet.
Even has a remote.

42:44.145 --> 42:45.480
- Unsanitary, but it's cool.
- [remote beeps]

42:45.563 --> 42:48.316
[groans] Stop, stop, stop.
Bad toilet, bad toilet.

42:48.400 --> 42:51.945
And last but not least,
TV in the minibar.

42:52.028 --> 42:52.862
[Hannah, Daryl] <i>Ooh!</i>

42:52.946 --> 42:55.323
[Hannah] <i>So, what's up with</i>
<i>the floor seats?</i>

42:55.407 --> 42:56.408
<i>You said courtside?</i>

42:56.491 --> 42:57.867
Well... [sighs]

42:57.951 --> 43:00.120
...you know, with the way
things have been going,

43:00.203 --> 43:02.247
if I'm even still on
the team in a week,

43:02.330 --> 43:04.582
I mean, I'll try to
find you some tickets.

43:06.209 --> 43:07.502
[blows raspberry]

43:07.585 --> 43:09.421
<i>Are you kidding me, bro?</i>

43:09.504 --> 43:10.338
<i>What do you mean,</i>

43:10.422 --> 43:12.299
<i>if you're going to be</i>
<i>on the team next week?</i>

43:12.382 --> 43:13.717
<i>You're on the actual Thorns.</i>

43:13.800 --> 43:15.552
<i>Ain't nobody kicking our boy</i>
<i>off the team.</i>

43:15.635 --> 43:16.678
<i>Nope.</i>

43:17.387 --> 43:19.973
<i>All right, that's it.</i>
<i>I need to hear it.</i>

43:20.056 --> 43:22.392
- Hear what?
- [chuckling] <i>Oh, you know what.</i>

43:22.475 --> 43:24.019
What? [sighs] Oh, come on.

43:24.102 --> 43:25.145
<i>Do it.</i>

43:25.228 --> 43:27.939
[sighs] Ba.

43:28.606 --> 43:30.066
<i>With feeling.</i>

43:30.942 --> 43:32.152
[bleats]

43:32.694 --> 43:34.070
[bleats]

43:34.154 --> 43:35.947
[bleats]

43:36.031 --> 43:37.699
[all bleating]

43:48.293 --> 43:49.878
[gasps] What?

43:49.961 --> 43:51.713
[bleating echoes]

43:52.714 --> 43:53.798
[bleats]

43:54.299 --> 43:55.633
[bleating continues]

43:55.717 --> 43:56.760
[screams]

43:56.843 --> 43:58.845
What is that noise?
Give me that!

43:58.928 --> 43:59.929
[bleating continues]

44:00.013 --> 44:00.930
<i>Jett...</i>

44:01.014 --> 44:02.682
<i>- Fillmore.</i>
<i>- Fillmore.</i>

44:02.766 --> 44:04.642
<i>Your head is so green--</i>

44:05.602 --> 44:08.063
Some of us have
a game to play tomorrow.

44:08.146 --> 44:09.939
Keep it down.

44:10.023 --> 44:11.691
- Uh, Jett, Jett.
- What?

44:11.775 --> 44:14.652
Um, I was hoping, up to you,

44:14.736 --> 44:19.324
I could get
a little playing time? Eh?

44:19.407 --> 44:21.368
- Oh, that's all?
- Mmm? Mmm?

44:21.451 --> 44:23.953
Just a little time on the court?

44:24.037 --> 44:27.582
Oh, kiddo.
All you had to do was ask.

44:27.665 --> 44:28.833
Really?

44:28.917 --> 44:30.585
[triumphant music playing]

44:33.380 --> 44:35.882
[Chuck] And we're back at
the Sunken City Cave,

44:35.965 --> 44:37.759
where stalactites
are falling from the ceiling,

44:37.842 --> 44:39.302
and the Thorns are at risk of

44:39.386 --> 44:41.221
falling out of
playoff contention.

44:41.304 --> 44:43.098
[crowd chanting]
Marshy! Marshy! Marshy!

44:43.181 --> 44:45.225
Whoa! Hey!

44:45.308 --> 44:46.309
[yelps]

44:46.393 --> 44:48.520
[squeaks, burps]

44:49.729 --> 44:50.814
[all cheering]

44:51.439 --> 44:53.191
[grunting]

44:56.486 --> 44:58.446
- [groans]
- [whistle blows]

44:58.530 --> 45:00.615
- Foul. Number three, Fillmore.
- Are you serious right now?

45:00.698 --> 45:01.741
Now you blow the whistle?

45:01.825 --> 45:04.494
One more word
and it's a technical!

45:04.577 --> 45:06.830
Why don't you
take that whistle... [growls]

45:06.913 --> 45:08.331
...and stick it right up
your cloaca.

45:08.415 --> 45:09.624
- [gasps]
- [whistle blows]

45:09.707 --> 45:12.627
Did she just say "cloaca"?
Can you say that on TV?

45:12.710 --> 45:15.130
Well, it's as close as
you can get to saying butth--

45:15.213 --> 45:16.548
[horn honking]

45:16.631 --> 45:18.842
[groans] We could've come back!

45:18.925 --> 45:20.844
I could have won this one.
[sighs]

45:20.927 --> 45:21.928
- [growls]
- [gasps]

45:22.011 --> 45:23.221
- Get up.
- Oh, no.

45:23.304 --> 45:25.515
- This feels bad.
- What are you waiting for?

45:26.641 --> 45:28.685
O-Oh, my gosh. [gasps]

45:28.768 --> 45:29.936
- You're putting me in?
- [growls]

45:30.019 --> 45:32.021
You think I want to?
I don't have a choice.

45:32.105 --> 45:34.065
- Otherwise, we forfeit the game.
- [yelps]

45:34.149 --> 45:35.525
[stammers]
They're putting in Will!

45:35.608 --> 45:38.027
- They're putting in Will!
- They're putting in Will!

45:38.111 --> 45:38.945
What?

45:39.028 --> 45:41.531
Hey, it's bedtime.
I thought I told you kids to--

45:41.614 --> 45:43.324
<i>Things are starting to get ugly</i>
<i>for the Thorns.</i>

45:43.408 --> 45:45.410
<i>You are the authority</i>
<i>on ugly, Chuck!</i>

45:45.493 --> 45:47.203
[children chanting]
Will, Will, Will, Will, Will.

45:47.287 --> 45:49.581
Oh, scoot over.
I gotta watch this.

45:49.664 --> 45:53.209
Just remember, an opportunity
like this is fleeting.

45:53.293 --> 45:57.297
But public humiliation,
that lives forever.

45:57.380 --> 45:59.090
Really? That's your pep talk?

45:59.174 --> 46:01.134
What? I... [sighs]
I haven't coached in a while.

46:01.217 --> 46:02.594
I'm sorry.
I'm a little out of practice.

46:02.677 --> 46:04.721
- [Will] Who says that?
- The whole planet's watching.

46:04.804 --> 46:06.681
Oh. That's worse.
Don't listen to me.

46:06.764 --> 46:08.308
[Rusty] <i>What a beautiful moment.</i>

46:08.391 --> 46:10.518
<i>The first small to play in Roar.</i>

46:11.060 --> 46:12.479
Yo, are you guarding me
or my shoelaces?

46:12.562 --> 46:14.022
I knew jerseys shrunk
in the wash,

46:14.105 --> 46:16.441
but I didn't know
the players did too! Aw.

46:16.524 --> 46:18.651
You're gonna end up
roadkill, kid.

46:18.735 --> 46:19.986
- [chuckles]
- [groans, panting]

46:20.069 --> 46:21.404
Yo, Archie! Pick left!

46:21.488 --> 46:22.864
- Switch it up!
- Hey, goat, good looking out!

46:26.201 --> 46:27.494
[Chuck] <i>Archie with a big block.</i>

46:27.577 --> 46:29.370
- I got it. I got it.
- [Rusty] <i>And Lenny recovers.</i>

46:29.454 --> 46:30.455
[rumbling]

46:31.331 --> 46:32.749
[Chuck] <i>Will Harris is</i>
<i>heading down the court.</i>

46:32.832 --> 46:34.959
Lenny! Hey, hey! I'm over here.
I'm open. I'm open.

46:35.043 --> 46:36.252
[Rusty]
<i>Lenny looking for somebody,</i>

46:36.336 --> 46:37.712
<i>- anyone who's not a goat.</i>
- [Will] Lenny!

46:37.795 --> 46:39.172
[Chuck]
<i>Nowhere to go but Harris.</i>

46:39.255 --> 46:41.341
[Rusty] <i>Lenny really doesn't</i>
<i>wanna throw that pass!</i>

46:41.424 --> 46:42.759
Let's go!

46:42.842 --> 46:43.760
[grunts]

46:49.599 --> 46:51.476
[Will] No, no, no, no, no, no.

46:57.232 --> 46:58.399
[panting]

46:59.692 --> 47:01.819
- [both growling]
- Uh...

47:01.903 --> 47:03.029
Shoot it, kid!

47:04.322 --> 47:06.115
[groaning, distorted]

47:07.492 --> 47:09.369
[panting, distorted]

47:16.543 --> 47:18.211
[ball bouncing, distorted]

47:18.294 --> 47:19.546
- [groans]
- [snarls]

47:19.629 --> 47:22.131
[both] Will just scored!

47:22.215 --> 47:24.133
[Chuck] <i>Will Harris becomes</i>
<i>the first small</i>

47:24.217 --> 47:26.636
<i>ever to score a point in Roar!</i>

47:26.719 --> 47:28.054
[triumphant music playing]

47:28.972 --> 47:30.014
- Take it back on D.
- [whistle blows]

47:30.098 --> 47:31.099
Did he just...

47:33.601 --> 47:34.602
[lion roars]

47:38.606 --> 47:40.108
- [Chuck] <i>Too easy!</i>
- Hey!

47:40.191 --> 47:42.402
- Did I upset the little goat?
- [crowd cheering]

47:42.485 --> 47:44.487
[announcer]
<i>Who wants goat tears?</i>

47:44.571 --> 47:46.948
[Mane] ♪ <i>Goat tears</i>
<i>You'll be crying goat tears </i>♪

47:47.031 --> 47:48.324
- [crowd booing]
- What? Oh, come on.

47:48.408 --> 47:51.578
Will! Hey, Will! Run Eagle 24.

47:51.661 --> 47:53.121
Thorns! Let's huddle up.

47:53.204 --> 47:54.872
What do we do?
W-What are we gonna do?

47:54.956 --> 47:57.542
Coach wants us to run Eagle 24.

47:57.625 --> 47:58.918
- We all know the play?
- Uh, no.

47:59.002 --> 48:01.296
- I do.
- I've eaten 24 eagles.

48:01.379 --> 48:02.255
- Excuse me, what?
- What?

48:02.338 --> 48:03.965
Okay, Lenny.
It's just you and me.

48:04.048 --> 48:05.049
I'm feeling something.

48:05.133 --> 48:07.093
I can't even describe it.
It's like I'm jittery.

48:07.176 --> 48:09.637
- Yeah. That's adrenaline.
- I kind of like it.

48:09.721 --> 48:12.390
Put the ball in play,
or I'm calling a delay of game.

48:12.473 --> 48:14.183
- Okay. Let's do this.
- [whistle blows]

48:14.267 --> 48:15.768
Run whatever play
you want, goat.

48:15.852 --> 48:17.270
I'm locking you down.

48:18.646 --> 48:19.772
- Come on, kid.
- [crowd cheering]

48:20.356 --> 48:22.233
[dramatic music playing]

48:29.782 --> 48:31.826
Will! [caws]

48:35.038 --> 48:36.414
[grunts]

48:37.874 --> 48:38.916
[buzzer sounds]

48:39.000 --> 48:40.501
[Rusty] <i>Thorns win!</i>

48:40.585 --> 48:42.295
Yeah! We just did that!

48:42.378 --> 48:44.005
["Light It Up" playing]

48:44.088 --> 48:47.800
- Lenny, yeah!
- All right! Yeah!

48:47.884 --> 48:50.178
Smalls in the building!

48:50.261 --> 48:52.889
Harris might be a small,
but he came up big!

48:52.972 --> 48:54.849
- [children] Yeah!
- Yeah!

48:54.932 --> 48:55.975
Whoo-hoo!

48:56.059 --> 48:58.144
I'm so happy, I could cry.

48:58.227 --> 48:59.854
Come on, Gerald. Let me see it.

48:59.937 --> 49:01.105
Yeah, okay.

49:01.189 --> 49:04.150
Yeah! Let's go!

49:04.233 --> 49:05.443
Oh, yeah!

49:05.526 --> 49:06.986
- Night, night, baby!
- No!

49:07.070 --> 49:08.696
- Anxious happy energy!
- Yeah!

49:08.780 --> 49:10.990
Anxious happy energy!

49:11.074 --> 49:14.160
[team members chanting]
Roots run deep! Roots run deep!

49:14.786 --> 49:17.955
[chuckles] What did I tell you?
He's got it!

49:20.667 --> 49:22.418
Come on, Jett. We won.

49:22.502 --> 49:25.088
Who wants to throw Dennis?

49:30.093 --> 49:31.094
[music ends]

49:31.969 --> 49:33.888
- [bleats]
- [crowd cheers]

49:35.682 --> 49:36.724
It's like they say, Chuck.

49:36.808 --> 49:37.850
You mess with the goat,

49:37.934 --> 49:39.769
you get a stalactite
to the face.

49:39.852 --> 49:41.229
That's not a catchphrase.

49:41.312 --> 49:43.147
Get off my cloaca, Chuck!

49:43.231 --> 49:45.483
[upbeat music playing]

49:48.403 --> 49:50.238
[Jett] Whatever. Whatever.

49:51.114 --> 49:53.074
I mean, I scored 33,
but who's keeping track?

49:53.157 --> 49:55.034
[chuckling]

49:55.118 --> 49:57.662
What...
Is it lame to search yourself?

49:57.745 --> 50:00.331
It is. [laughs] I know.
I can't help myself.

50:00.415 --> 50:02.291
Yo, goat. Nice work tonight.

50:02.375 --> 50:04.085
You wanna join?

50:04.168 --> 50:06.212
- Who, me?
- Come on.

50:06.295 --> 50:07.547
Get to know your teammates
a little.

50:07.630 --> 50:08.506
We don't bite.

50:08.589 --> 50:10.633
- Well, Modo does sometimes.
- [rasps]

50:10.717 --> 50:11.718
Just get in here.

50:11.801 --> 50:13.803
We're extending an
olive branch here.

50:13.886 --> 50:17.181
Well, I am grabbing
that olive branch. [chuckles]

50:17.265 --> 50:18.266
[groans]

50:18.349 --> 50:21.269
All right, ante up.
Don't be shy now, rook.

50:21.352 --> 50:25.440
Shy? This kid's got ice
in his veins, raining treys.

50:25.523 --> 50:27.775
- [chuckles]
- It was just one trey.

50:27.859 --> 50:29.610
Honestly, when Jett
crashed out of the game,

50:29.694 --> 50:31.112
I thought it was over.

50:31.195 --> 50:33.990
Oh, for sure.
But the goat came through.

50:34.073 --> 50:34.907
My guy!

50:34.991 --> 50:36.492
I didn't even need
my bucket tonight.

50:36.576 --> 50:38.327
This is so cool!

50:38.411 --> 50:40.663
- [team members chuckling]
- [sighs]

50:40.747 --> 50:42.373
All right. All right. Uh...

50:42.457 --> 50:44.709
Uh, should we ask Jett to play?

50:44.792 --> 50:47.628
Hey! You trying to ruin
the one piece of fun we got?

50:47.712 --> 50:49.964
[Olivia] We won without Jett.

50:50.047 --> 50:52.008
I can't believe we're actually
talking like this.

50:52.091 --> 50:53.843
She could be listening.

50:53.926 --> 50:58.181
["Meow" playing]

50:58.264 --> 50:59.474
What? Why?

50:59.557 --> 51:02.518
When we win, she likes to
be the one that won the win.

51:02.602 --> 51:05.480
She's a winner, and she's
going to get us to the playoffs.

51:05.563 --> 51:06.564
[chuckles]

51:06.647 --> 51:09.400
We got lucky for one game.

51:09.484 --> 51:11.110
Let's not go mad.

51:11.194 --> 51:13.696
I appreciate the optimism,
but look at this team.

51:13.780 --> 51:15.948
We got Coach Dennis at the helm.

51:16.032 --> 51:18.201
- I think he dies when he sleeps.
- [snoring]

51:18.284 --> 51:22.538
Me? I'm just trying to focus
on my sweet baby angels.

51:22.622 --> 51:24.874
- Incoming! [giggles]
- [farts]

51:24.957 --> 51:26.501
[screaming]

51:26.584 --> 51:28.586
- We saved your life.
- [giggling]

51:28.669 --> 51:30.588
- Oh, my gosh.
- Everybody just sees me

51:30.671 --> 51:33.341
as a tall rebound robot.

51:33.424 --> 51:35.384
At a certain point,
I just checked out.

51:35.468 --> 51:37.595
I started finding other ways
to be creative.

51:37.678 --> 51:39.263
Lenny is a rapper.

51:39.347 --> 51:41.557
Ah, Olivia, stop trying to
put me on front street.

51:41.641 --> 51:43.768
You know it's nothing
I take too seriously.

51:43.851 --> 51:45.019
[hip-hop playing]

51:46.187 --> 51:47.188
[Lenny caws]

51:47.271 --> 51:49.732
Okay, maybe I take it
a little seriously.

51:49.816 --> 51:52.777
And I'm a bust. Maybe
the biggest in Roar history.

51:52.860 --> 51:54.737
Come on now, Liv.
That ain't true.

51:54.821 --> 51:56.656
It is. You can say it.

51:56.739 --> 51:58.407
What else do you call
a number one pick

51:58.491 --> 51:59.575
whose biggest claim to fame

51:59.659 --> 52:01.494
is being on
someone else's poster?

52:01.577 --> 52:02.745
Olivia?

52:02.829 --> 52:06.332
Listen. Point is, this squad
is a bunch of head cases,

52:06.415 --> 52:09.252
has-beens,
and whatever the heck Modo is.

52:09.335 --> 52:11.003
Modo is icon.

52:11.546 --> 52:13.840
All right, Care Bear.
Bets are in.

52:13.923 --> 52:15.591
What you got?

52:15.675 --> 52:17.468
[dramatic music playing]

52:22.890 --> 52:24.809
- I fold.
- I fold.

52:24.892 --> 52:27.436
Ah! Uno reverse.

52:28.521 --> 52:31.983
- Uno, Uno, Uno! Uno, Uno, Uno.
- Modo. Wrong game!

52:32.066 --> 52:34.443
<i>Yeah, they're</i>
<i>the absolute worst.</i>

52:34.527 --> 52:37.488
- <i>Oh. Oh, hi!</i>
- Oh, hi, Flo.

52:37.572 --> 52:38.489
- Hey, Flo!
- Hi, Flo.

52:38.573 --> 52:40.700
- [Archie] Hey, boss.
- Hi, piglet.

52:40.783 --> 52:42.743
<i>Ugh. Hi, Modo.</i>

52:42.827 --> 52:44.453
<i>Anyways...</i> [blowing]

52:44.537 --> 52:46.789
<i>Great team win last night.</i>

52:46.873 --> 52:50.585
<i>Socials are blowing up,</i>
<i>and I've got some exciting news.</i>

52:50.668 --> 52:52.545
<i>Hey, is Jett there?</i>

52:52.628 --> 52:54.005
- <i>Jett?</i>
- What?

52:54.088 --> 52:55.214
- <i>Jett?</i>
- What?

52:55.298 --> 52:56.382
- <i>Jett!</i>
- What?

52:56.465 --> 52:59.927
<i>Oh, hi. You know that</i>
<i>Jett promo tomorrow?</i>

53:00.011 --> 53:02.763
<i>Well, now</i>
<i>you're all gonna be in it.</i>

53:02.847 --> 53:03.890
[all cheering]

53:03.973 --> 53:07.184
- Oh, yeah. Oh, this is dope.
- [growling]

53:07.268 --> 53:10.688
["Meow" playing]

53:10.771 --> 53:12.106
[song ends]

53:14.609 --> 53:16.444
[dramatic music playing]

53:16.527 --> 53:20.781
[commentator]
<i>In Vineland, our roots run deep.</i>

53:21.824 --> 53:24.785
<i>Vineland didn't just invent</i>
<i>the game of roarball.</i>

53:24.869 --> 53:26.704
<i>We define it.</i>

53:27.371 --> 53:29.749
No one gets by me in the lane.

53:29.832 --> 53:31.751
I don't play the long game.

53:31.834 --> 53:33.544
I play the tall game.

53:33.628 --> 53:35.880
Can't catch me on a fast break.

53:35.963 --> 53:38.674
[chuckles] I make you feel weird

53:39.175 --> 53:41.052
and you're not sure why.

53:41.594 --> 53:43.095
And I'm the best in the game.

53:43.179 --> 53:44.889
[commentator]
<i>It's the end of one era</i>

53:44.972 --> 53:47.725
<i>and the beginning of another.</i>

53:48.225 --> 53:50.353
It's my time now.

53:50.436 --> 53:54.106
And now, it's time to
pass the torch to the new GO--

53:54.190 --> 53:56.400
- [groans] GOAT!
- [stammering]

53:56.484 --> 53:59.153
[retching]

53:59.236 --> 54:00.863
I'm sorry. I can't.
I can't. I... This...

54:00.947 --> 54:02.823
- My body is rejecting the word.
- [director] Cut!

54:02.907 --> 54:03.991
You know what,
let's just take five.

54:04.075 --> 54:06.077
Cut! Jett, baby,
what's the problem?

54:06.160 --> 54:07.870
The problem is I'm the GOAT.

54:07.954 --> 54:10.247
I'm not passing the torch

54:10.331 --> 54:12.249
'cause I'm still playing.
[blows]

54:12.333 --> 54:15.044
It's just a promo.
It's a play on words.

54:15.127 --> 54:17.254
He's a goat but also
wants to be the GOAT.

54:17.338 --> 54:18.381
Just say the lines.

54:18.464 --> 54:20.758
Are we all okay with this?

54:20.841 --> 54:22.009
Now, I want to see
a show of paws.

54:22.093 --> 54:24.845
Raise 'em up!
Who is okay with this?

54:24.929 --> 54:27.139
[chuckles] Oh, everybody? Okay.

54:27.223 --> 54:30.101
Hey, Maximus, let's pick it up
from "they define it."

54:30.726 --> 54:31.978
- You got it, boss.
- [beeping]

54:32.061 --> 54:32.895
[clears throat]

54:32.979 --> 54:34.313
[deep voice]
Vineland didn't just

54:34.397 --> 54:35.898
invent the game of roarball.

54:35.982 --> 54:37.483
We define it.

54:37.566 --> 54:39.652
I block every shot.

54:39.735 --> 54:42.196
I'm unstoppable. I think.

54:42.279 --> 54:45.199
And I think there is
a power struggle happening.

54:45.282 --> 54:47.451
- [Maximus] <i>The end of one era...</i>
- I'm the GOAT.

54:47.535 --> 54:49.662
<i>...and the beginning of another</i>
<i>that's even better.</i>

54:49.745 --> 54:50.746
It's my time--

54:50.830 --> 54:51.956
- No, it's not.
- Cut!

54:52.039 --> 54:53.749
- Just say the line, Jett.
- [bell ringing]

54:53.833 --> 54:55.626
- No! It's not true.
- I don't think you understand

54:55.710 --> 54:57.420
the difference between
figurative and literal.

54:57.503 --> 54:59.296
It's a double goat meaning.

54:59.380 --> 55:00.923
I don't care. I'm not saying it!

55:01.007 --> 55:02.425
- And he's not saying it either!
- [sighs]

55:02.508 --> 55:05.636
And y'all don't even think
about saying it. Capisce?

55:05.720 --> 55:08.639
[Maximus] <i>Vineland didn't just</i>
<i>invent the game of roarball.</i>

55:08.723 --> 55:09.807
- <i>We define it.</i>
- [sobbing]

55:09.890 --> 55:12.601
I just wanna be a good dad.

55:12.685 --> 55:14.979
I just wanna blow minds
with sick rhymes.

55:15.062 --> 55:17.231
Whoever memes my beak,

55:17.314 --> 55:18.774
you will be hearing from
my lawyer.

55:18.858 --> 55:20.860
I don't even know
the rules of roarball.

55:20.943 --> 55:21.777
I'm the GOAT.

55:21.861 --> 55:23.404
Always have been,
always will be.

55:23.487 --> 55:25.031
Not some little goat guy.

55:25.114 --> 55:27.324
- It's a single goat meaning.
- [director] Cut!

55:27.408 --> 55:28.409
- Cut, cut!
- [bell ringing]

55:28.492 --> 55:30.036
Look, since you're not
gonna say the line,

55:30.119 --> 55:31.871
why don't you just give us
a little "Baa."

55:31.954 --> 55:33.664
Oh, I am not saying that.

55:33.748 --> 55:35.499
Why do I bother you so much?

55:35.583 --> 55:38.836
[growls] You just got here, son.
Who even are you?

55:38.919 --> 55:41.338
I'm the one who stepped up
when you fouled out.

55:41.422 --> 55:42.465
We finally won,

55:42.548 --> 55:43.758
and you weren't even
on the court.

55:43.841 --> 55:45.384
- [gasps]
- [feedback screeches]

55:45.468 --> 55:46.677
Now I feel weird.

55:46.761 --> 55:48.596
Is this how
I make everyone feel?

55:48.679 --> 55:50.222
[growls, sighs]

55:50.306 --> 55:51.640
You know what, superstar?

55:51.724 --> 55:53.809
This looks like
it's your promo now.

55:53.893 --> 55:56.145
'Cause I'm out of here. Yeah.

55:56.645 --> 55:58.731
- Good luck selling tickets.
- [door opens, slams]

56:01.108 --> 56:03.944
Jett! Wait.
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to--

56:04.028 --> 56:05.613
I didn't sign up
for that, all right?

56:05.696 --> 56:07.823
Come on, Jett,
it's just a promo.

56:07.907 --> 56:09.825
It gets fans hyped for our game!

56:09.909 --> 56:10.910
But it's not.

56:11.535 --> 56:13.120
It's how everyone treats me.

56:13.621 --> 56:14.872
They all want me to
pass the torch,

56:14.955 --> 56:16.332
but I'm not done!

56:16.415 --> 56:17.458
There she is. Hey, Mom...

56:17.541 --> 56:19.376
I'm still here!
I'm still playing!

56:19.460 --> 56:21.420
We're still waiting on
that Claw, Fillmore.

56:21.504 --> 56:22.880
You're better off on the bench.

56:22.963 --> 56:24.048
- What?
- [fan 1] I love you, Jett!

56:24.131 --> 56:25.633
I just want my car.
Where is my driver?

56:25.716 --> 56:26.759
[fan 2] Jett! Over here!

56:26.842 --> 56:29.220
- Follow me.
- [fan 3] Jett Fillmore!

56:29.303 --> 56:31.472
[fan 4] Hey, Jett.
Why do you not win anymore?

56:31.555 --> 56:33.224
["Grandmaster" playing]

56:33.766 --> 56:35.101
[pedestrian 1] Hey, watch it!

56:35.184 --> 56:37.019
- [Will gulps]
- [growls]

56:37.895 --> 56:38.896
[pedestrian 2] Excuse me.

56:38.979 --> 56:40.898
[all groaning]

56:40.981 --> 56:42.233
This way.

56:42.900 --> 56:44.401
Whoa. This kid can move.

56:45.486 --> 56:47.029
- [music continues]
- [groans]

56:49.865 --> 56:50.741
[roars]

56:52.118 --> 56:53.119
[music ends]

56:58.207 --> 56:59.875
[both chuckling]

56:59.959 --> 57:01.335
I've never broken
the law before.

57:01.418 --> 57:03.295
- [grunts]
- I feel so alive.

57:03.379 --> 57:05.422
I actually paid for
both of our rides.

57:05.506 --> 57:06.882
I just wanted to see you sweat.

57:06.966 --> 57:09.260
- [chuckles, groans]
- [chuckles]

57:11.929 --> 57:12.930
[melancholy music playing]

57:13.013 --> 57:14.265
It was so messed up back there.

57:14.348 --> 57:17.017
I mean, they act like
you've been losing forever!

57:17.101 --> 57:18.185
I don't know
what's wrong with them,

57:18.269 --> 57:20.062
b-but I remember
the Furball game.

57:20.146 --> 57:22.857
That was amazing!
You scored 70 points!

57:22.940 --> 57:25.359
Well, you know why they call it
the Furball game, right?

57:26.318 --> 57:29.697
Because I choked.
I missed the last shot.

57:30.364 --> 57:31.574
We didn't make the Claw.

57:32.491 --> 57:36.453
Ever since then, Vineland's got
no love for Jett Fillmore.

57:36.537 --> 57:38.831
No love for Jett Fillmore?
[stammers]

57:38.914 --> 57:41.333
You're seriously gonna listen
to a couple of haters?

57:41.417 --> 57:42.918
Where's the lie? Even I get it.

57:43.002 --> 57:44.003
[chime on PA]

57:44.086 --> 57:46.463
[announcer]
<i>Next stop, Vineland City Center.</i>

57:46.547 --> 57:47.882
Okay. Get up.

57:47.965 --> 57:49.550
We're getting off right here.

57:52.928 --> 57:54.221
[trumpets]

57:54.889 --> 57:55.806
[dings]

57:59.977 --> 58:01.645
- [patron] Hey, there he is!
- [all clamoring]

58:01.729 --> 58:03.022
Oh.

58:03.105 --> 58:05.191
You come to pick up
some extra shifts?

58:05.274 --> 58:07.818
Ah. [chuckles]
I see you got jokes.

58:07.902 --> 58:09.236
[Daryl] Come back empty-handed?

58:09.320 --> 58:12.698
You said you'd get me
Jett Fillmore's autograph.

58:12.781 --> 58:14.867
[whispers] Oh, my gosh.
It's Jett Fillmore.

58:14.950 --> 58:15.993
- [all gasping]
- What's up, y'all?

58:16.076 --> 58:17.536
Jett said
she'd never tried the pie,

58:17.620 --> 58:19.371
so I figured we'd pull up.

58:19.455 --> 58:21.248
[chuckles, gasps]

58:21.332 --> 58:22.625
This is...

58:22.708 --> 58:23.709
[uplifting music playing]

58:23.792 --> 58:25.336
Whoa.

58:26.462 --> 58:27.713
[Will] Not bad, huh?

58:30.216 --> 58:32.593
Wait, is that
my high school jersey?

58:32.676 --> 58:35.930
Dang, y'all are some
crazy stalkers.

58:36.013 --> 58:37.014
[all chuckling]

58:37.097 --> 58:38.766
[chuckling]

58:41.477 --> 58:43.854
What do we have here? No way.

58:43.938 --> 58:45.898
Is that you? [chuckles, sighs]

58:45.981 --> 58:48.984
[chuckles] Hey, you wanna
meet the others?

58:50.194 --> 58:52.738
My grandpappy came here
from afar

58:52.821 --> 58:55.908
to help build
the Greenhouse. Yes.

58:55.991 --> 58:59.078
That's little me right there
in my diaper.

58:59.161 --> 59:00.663
W-Wow.

59:00.746 --> 59:02.373
We're gonna name
our baby after you, Jett!

59:02.456 --> 59:04.375
We're hoping she'll grow up
to be just like you.

59:04.458 --> 59:06.627
Aw. Cute egg.

59:06.710 --> 59:07.711
Check this out!

59:07.795 --> 59:09.922
When I move my shoulders,
it looks like you're dunking.

59:10.005 --> 59:11.423
Oh... [retches] Yeah.

59:11.507 --> 59:15.052
Um... It definitely looks like
I am doing something.

59:15.135 --> 59:16.011
[bell dings]

59:16.095 --> 59:17.388
[Jett] Okay, so
we're down by two, right?

59:17.471 --> 59:19.181
I'm nauseous.

59:19.265 --> 59:21.141
It's like that every time
I go to open my mouth,

59:21.225 --> 59:22.601
it's like... [gasping]
...here it comes.

59:22.685 --> 59:24.520
- I can't even see straight.
- I knew it! I knew it!

59:24.603 --> 59:25.854
I could tell something was off.

59:25.938 --> 59:27.189
How did you get so sick?

59:27.273 --> 59:30.317
Look, I'm not gonna say
it's true,

59:30.401 --> 59:34.822
but I will say the delivery guy
was wearing a Magma jersey.

59:34.905 --> 59:36.490
- [all gasping]
- Coinkydink? You decide.

59:36.573 --> 59:38.409
[Will] Drumroll, please.

59:38.492 --> 59:40.577
- [drumming]
- [swallows]

59:42.079 --> 59:43.998
- [all cheering]
- Right? Right? I told you.

59:44.540 --> 59:46.959
Oh, snap. The Fillmore 1's?

59:47.042 --> 59:48.335
Where did you get these?

59:48.419 --> 59:51.297
A collector
never reveals her secrets.

59:51.380 --> 59:52.506
[chuckles] Just kidding.

59:52.589 --> 59:54.717
I got 'em from the store
when they came out.

59:54.800 --> 59:56.468
I've been looking everywhere
for these.

59:56.552 --> 59:58.053
O-Okay, how much
do you want for 'em?

59:58.137 --> 59:59.263
Are you kidding me?

59:59.346 --> 01:00:00.556
Your money's no good here.

01:00:00.639 --> 01:00:03.142
They're your shoe.
Just take 'em.

01:00:03.225 --> 01:00:04.643
No. No.

01:00:04.727 --> 01:00:07.021
Just bring back a Claw.

01:00:07.104 --> 01:00:08.856
[purrs] Deal.

01:00:09.565 --> 01:00:10.858
[patrons] Bye, Jett!

01:00:10.941 --> 01:00:12.067
Later, y'all.

01:00:12.151 --> 01:00:13.777
How did you know about
that spot?

01:00:13.861 --> 01:00:15.863
I, uh... I go there for the pie.

01:00:15.946 --> 01:00:18.449
It delivers every time.

01:00:18.532 --> 01:00:20.200
- Oh.
- [chuckles]

01:00:20.284 --> 01:00:21.493
You were the delivery boy.

01:00:21.577 --> 01:00:25.039
Yeah, yeah. [exhales]
Was that a little too obvious?

01:00:25.122 --> 01:00:26.248
Okay.

01:00:26.790 --> 01:00:28.876
- [exhales]
- I mean...

01:00:28.959 --> 01:00:29.960
[sighs]

01:00:31.170 --> 01:00:32.546
The real reason I know the diner

01:00:32.629 --> 01:00:34.381
<i>is because my mom</i>
<i>used to work there.</i>

01:00:34.840 --> 01:00:37.009
- <i>She was a huge Thorns fan.</i>
- [Mom kissing]

01:00:37.092 --> 01:00:39.219
- Mom.
- That's for every year. [kisses]

01:00:39.303 --> 01:00:42.264
Happy birthday, Will. [chuckles]

01:00:42.348 --> 01:00:47.353
Baby, you know you could wish
for anything, so dream big.

01:00:47.853 --> 01:00:50.022
You're not just going to
play roarball.

01:00:50.773 --> 01:00:54.651
You're gonna change the game.
[kisses]

01:00:54.735 --> 01:00:55.903
Dream big.

01:00:55.986 --> 01:00:58.238
- [inhales, blows]
- [patrons cheering]

01:01:00.699 --> 01:01:03.285
[Will] <i>Then, she got sick.</i>

01:01:04.745 --> 01:01:06.663
[blows]

01:01:07.664 --> 01:01:10.167
<i>And Vineland stepped up for me.</i>

01:01:12.544 --> 01:01:14.671
Roarball was where I went
to get out of my head

01:01:15.381 --> 01:01:17.841
and just... play.

01:01:17.925 --> 01:01:19.343
Y-You know?

01:01:19.426 --> 01:01:21.011
And everyone thought
I was tripping when

01:01:21.095 --> 01:01:23.639
I said I wanted to be
a roarball player.

01:01:24.139 --> 01:01:27.351
Everybody. Except for my mom.

01:01:31.772 --> 01:01:34.483
And I want her to be right.

01:01:36.610 --> 01:01:37.861
[car door opens]

01:01:40.072 --> 01:01:42.074
You got a lot of
good folks behind you.

01:01:44.451 --> 01:01:45.577
So do you.

01:01:48.122 --> 01:01:49.581
- [sighs]
- [car door closes]

01:01:51.667 --> 01:01:53.127
See you at practice tomorrow.

01:02:03.387 --> 01:02:04.304
[Jett purring]

01:02:10.144 --> 01:02:12.771
<i>Hey, yo. It's Mane season.</i>

01:02:12.855 --> 01:02:14.064
Oh, no. Here we go.

01:02:14.148 --> 01:02:15.691
<i>And you know, man,</i>
<i>just at the barbershop</i>

01:02:15.774 --> 01:02:17.317
<i>with P-Dogg and Boogie.</i>

01:02:17.401 --> 01:02:18.402
<i>Let's get into it.</i>

01:02:18.485 --> 01:02:20.821
<i>A lot of naysayers</i>
<i>out there, folks,</i>

01:02:20.904 --> 01:02:23.282
<i>been talkin' about</i>
<i>this big game the goat had.</i>

01:02:23.365 --> 01:02:26.285
<i>Puttin' up a whole three points.</i>
<i>He's trash.</i>

01:02:26.368 --> 01:02:28.162
<i>Thorns are trash!</i>
<i>Thorns are trash!</i>

01:02:28.245 --> 01:02:30.122
<i>And it ain't just the goat</i>
<i>that's wack.</i>

01:02:30.205 --> 01:02:31.832
<i>The whole team is cooked!</i>

01:02:31.915 --> 01:02:33.250
- <i>They trash.</i>
- Mm-mmm.

01:02:33.333 --> 01:02:34.710
Someone needs to
shut this clown up

01:02:34.793 --> 01:02:36.044
- once and for all.
- [phone chimes]

01:02:36.128 --> 01:02:39.423
<i>Hold up! Looks like we got</i>
<i>a special chat request.</i> [laughs]

01:02:39.465 --> 01:02:42.593
<i>It's the grandmama herself,</i>
<i>Jett Fillmore.</i>

01:02:42.676 --> 01:02:45.888
Yo, yo, yo!
Mane is on live with Jett!

01:02:45.971 --> 01:02:47.639
What? Let me see that.
[swallows]

01:02:47.723 --> 01:02:48.765
[gasps]

01:02:48.849 --> 01:02:50.726
No way, bro-dents.

01:02:50.809 --> 01:02:52.519
Do you know what?
I'm just surprised

01:02:52.603 --> 01:02:54.271
you even know how to
use your phone

01:02:54.354 --> 01:02:55.397
for anything other than

01:02:55.481 --> 01:02:57.524
reading a menu
with the flashlight.

01:02:57.608 --> 01:02:59.401
I'm surprised you can talk
with teeth like that.

01:02:59.485 --> 01:03:01.445
Your tongue over there
lookin' like it's in jail.

01:03:01.528 --> 01:03:02.779
"Let me out. Let me out."

01:03:02.863 --> 01:03:03.864
[all] Oh!

01:03:03.947 --> 01:03:05.866
[chuckling] Jett's got bars.

01:03:05.949 --> 01:03:08.076
I've been in the league
five years,

01:03:08.160 --> 01:03:09.870
already got two Claws.

01:03:09.953 --> 01:03:11.246
How many Claws you got?

01:03:11.330 --> 01:03:13.624
- Nada. [exclaims, cackles]
- Ball don't lie. Ball don't lie.

01:03:13.707 --> 01:03:15.042
Well, that's about to change.

01:03:15.125 --> 01:03:16.710
I don't know if you saw
our last game,

01:03:16.793 --> 01:03:19.254
but Will is
shooting straight fire.

01:03:19.338 --> 01:03:20.339
<i>Archie is a beast,</i>

01:03:20.422 --> 01:03:22.174
<i>Olivia got her confidence back,</i>

01:03:22.257 --> 01:03:23.258
<i>Lenny's a stopper</i>

01:03:23.342 --> 01:03:24.635
- <i>and Modo is an icon.</i>
- Hey!

01:03:24.718 --> 01:03:26.595
The Thorns are about to win
our next eight games

01:03:26.678 --> 01:03:28.096
and then, yeah,
we're coming for the Claw.

01:03:28.180 --> 01:03:29.181
[all gasping]

01:03:29.264 --> 01:03:31.099
[chuckling] Girl, you crazy.

01:03:31.183 --> 01:03:33.352
Only thing crazy is
that Clydesdale hair

01:03:33.435 --> 01:03:34.728
that you got sewn into
your head.

01:03:34.811 --> 01:03:36.355
- Yeah, the textures don't match.
- [growls]

01:03:36.438 --> 01:03:37.856
- Drag him, Jett.
- [chuckling]

01:03:37.940 --> 01:03:38.941
- Oh!
- [chuckling]

01:03:39.024 --> 01:03:41.777
- Textures don't match.
- Hey, guys, don't diss the hair.

01:03:41.860 --> 01:03:43.070
You know I get sensitive.

01:03:43.153 --> 01:03:43.987
- Oh!
- Jett!

01:03:44.071 --> 01:03:45.489
- Wait till I get off this live.
- [laughs] Hmm.

01:03:45.572 --> 01:03:46.406
You know what,

01:03:46.490 --> 01:03:48.659
I hope you make a run
so I can wreck you,

01:03:48.742 --> 01:03:51.245
just like I wrecked
that baby goat at the Cage.

01:03:51.328 --> 01:03:54.248
Until then, keep Will
and the Thorns out your mouth.

01:03:54.331 --> 01:03:55.499
These roots run deep!

01:03:55.999 --> 01:03:57.084
Fillmore out.

01:03:58.460 --> 01:03:59.503
These roots run deep!

01:03:59.586 --> 01:04:01.421
[all chanting]
Roots run deep! Roots run deep!

01:04:01.505 --> 01:04:02.548
Roots run deep!

01:04:02.631 --> 01:04:05.884
Roots run deep! Roots run deep!
Roots run deep!

01:04:09.513 --> 01:04:11.306
[inhales, exhales]

01:04:11.390 --> 01:04:12.391
- [all cheering]
- [chuckling]

01:04:12.474 --> 01:04:13.892
Yeah, mama!

01:04:14.476 --> 01:04:15.811
[chuckles]

01:04:15.894 --> 01:04:18.272
You said some
pretty nice stuff about us.

01:04:18.814 --> 01:04:20.148
I'm wondering why.

01:04:20.232 --> 01:04:21.275
Are you feeling okay?

01:04:21.358 --> 01:04:22.859
It's the first time
I've been tagged

01:04:22.943 --> 01:04:24.820
in something that
didn't make me cry.

01:04:25.320 --> 01:04:26.989
I don't trust it.

01:04:27.072 --> 01:04:28.574
Did you mean it?

01:04:29.825 --> 01:04:32.578
Look, I meant
every word that I said.

01:04:32.661 --> 01:04:34.162
I really do need y'all.

01:04:34.246 --> 01:04:37.207
And it's time
I finally acknowledged

01:04:37.291 --> 01:04:40.252
that I've got some
really good folks behind me.

01:04:40.335 --> 01:04:41.420
- [chuckling]
- Yeah.

01:04:41.503 --> 01:04:42.754
Really?

01:04:42.838 --> 01:04:44.381
To show you how serious I am,

01:04:44.423 --> 01:04:46.633
I'm ready to
shake some things up.

01:04:48.343 --> 01:04:50.971
I'm officially naming Dennis

01:04:51.054 --> 01:04:52.806
the new head coach
of the Thorns.

01:04:52.889 --> 01:04:54.808
[uplifting music playing]

01:04:54.891 --> 01:04:57.477
But I'm already head coach.

01:04:57.561 --> 01:05:00.105
I know. But now, it's, like,
for real this time.

01:05:00.188 --> 01:05:01.773
You're gonna be head coach.
Only coach.

01:05:01.857 --> 01:05:03.233
[chuckles]

01:05:03.317 --> 01:05:04.610
The team is yours, Dennis.

01:05:04.693 --> 01:05:07.029
- [all cheering]
- Yeah, man!

01:05:08.238 --> 01:05:09.656
Let's go, baby. Give it up.

01:05:09.740 --> 01:05:11.908
My therapist said this day
would never come. Uh...

01:05:12.492 --> 01:05:13.535
Just give me a second.

01:05:14.036 --> 01:05:16.330
Dennis, get it together.
Get it together.

01:05:16.413 --> 01:05:18.332
Get. It. Together.

01:05:18.457 --> 01:05:20.542
[grunting, screams]

01:05:20.626 --> 01:05:22.210
[panting]

01:05:23.545 --> 01:05:28.550
I've been watching, learning,
waiting for this day.

01:05:28.634 --> 01:05:30.135
- I'm scared.
- [both] We like it.

01:05:30.218 --> 01:05:34.806
We are going to rip the heart
out of this league

01:05:34.890 --> 01:05:36.558
and make 'em look at it.

01:05:36.642 --> 01:05:37.934
[chuckles] Nice.

01:05:38.018 --> 01:05:42.814
Welcome to
Dennis's world of pain.

01:05:42.898 --> 01:05:45.108
[cackling]

01:05:46.318 --> 01:05:49.071
Archie, you don't have to worry
about your little girls

01:05:49.154 --> 01:05:50.656
growing up
with violent tendencies.

01:05:50.739 --> 01:05:52.324
Charge! [giggling]

01:05:52.407 --> 01:05:55.994
They've gone full-tilt
365-days-a-year psychopath.

01:05:56.078 --> 01:05:58.664
Actually, it's 364.

01:05:58.747 --> 01:06:00.290
We take Christmas off.

01:06:00.374 --> 01:06:02.125
Stop thinking of yourself
as an enforcer.

01:06:02.209 --> 01:06:04.211
You're a protector.

01:06:04.294 --> 01:06:07.214
<i>Your teammates are like</i>
<i>your daughters too.</i>

01:06:07.297 --> 01:06:08.298
<i>Protect them.</i>

01:06:08.382 --> 01:06:10.467
[Archie] Hey, hands off
my beautiful daughter.

01:06:10.550 --> 01:06:11.635
Good looking out, Archie.

01:06:11.718 --> 01:06:13.011
Wait, what did you just call me?

01:06:13.887 --> 01:06:17.349
Lenny, team after team
used you for your height

01:06:17.432 --> 01:06:18.642
and threw you away.

01:06:18.725 --> 01:06:20.394
So you lost your drive.

01:06:20.477 --> 01:06:22.688
Ten teams in ten years, Coach.

01:06:22.771 --> 01:06:25.190
Well, this team has your back.

01:06:25.273 --> 01:06:27.484
So stick your neck out for them.

01:06:27.567 --> 01:06:28.819
<i>Now tear the roof off</i>
<i>this mother!</i>

01:06:28.902 --> 01:06:30.654
- [squawks]
- [gasps]

01:06:35.200 --> 01:06:36.034
[Lenny] Bang!

01:06:36.118 --> 01:06:38.370
- Nice one, Lenny.
- That's my squad.

01:06:38.453 --> 01:06:39.496
That's my squad.

01:06:39.579 --> 01:06:41.748
Ooh, I kind of like that.

01:06:41.832 --> 01:06:42.791
Olivia.

01:06:42.874 --> 01:06:44.251
- One second. I'm just...
- [keyboard clicking]

01:06:44.334 --> 01:06:45.502
[Dennis] Seriously,
give me your phone.

01:06:45.585 --> 01:06:47.629
- Oh, no.
- You are never seeing it again.

01:06:47.713 --> 01:06:48.964
[whimpers]

01:06:49.047 --> 01:06:50.048
Another phone?

01:06:50.132 --> 01:06:52.676
Where are you getting
all these phones?

01:06:52.759 --> 01:06:56.430
Olivia, get your head out of
the phone and into the game!

01:06:56.513 --> 01:06:57.889
[groans] Ugh.

01:06:58.432 --> 01:06:59.433
- [rasps]
- [chuckles]

01:06:59.516 --> 01:07:02.227
You were drafted number one
for a reason.

01:07:02.310 --> 01:07:04.938
The only thing
holding you back is you.

01:07:05.021 --> 01:07:07.774
You are still that bird.

01:07:12.028 --> 01:07:14.114
I am that bird.

01:07:14.656 --> 01:07:16.116
Will. Jett.

01:07:16.199 --> 01:07:18.952
[chuckling] I'm gonna coach
the scat out of you.

01:07:19.035 --> 01:07:21.204
- Dennis, there's kids here.
- [both] Scat! Scat! Scat!

01:07:21.288 --> 01:07:23.081
Jett, remember
these three words,

01:07:23.165 --> 01:07:25.625
"Pass the ball."

01:07:25.709 --> 01:07:27.961
- Like, let the ball go?
- Jett.

01:07:28.044 --> 01:07:30.380
You mean share? With the others?

01:07:30.464 --> 01:07:31.715
I don't think this lesson
is for me.

01:07:31.798 --> 01:07:33.300
- Trust your team.
- [Will] Open!

01:07:33.383 --> 01:07:34.926
- [Dennis] Jett, pass the ball.
- [whistle blows]

01:07:35.010 --> 01:07:36.720
[groans]
It's harder than it looks.

01:07:36.803 --> 01:07:38.388
[Will] I'm open.

01:07:38.472 --> 01:07:41.433
- [Dennis] Pass it!
- What? [meows, whimpers]

01:07:41.516 --> 01:07:42.893
- Jett.
- I got it. I got it.

01:07:42.976 --> 01:07:44.811
- Pass the ball, Jett.
- [Jett] No, no, no, no.

01:07:44.895 --> 01:07:48.273
Dennis. No, no, Dennis.
[meows] No, no, no. Dennis!

01:07:49.024 --> 01:07:50.025
[growls]

01:07:51.109 --> 01:07:52.110
[groans]

01:07:52.778 --> 01:07:54.154
Yes! Yes!

01:07:54.237 --> 01:07:57.115
Now just do that
500,000 more times.

01:07:57.199 --> 01:07:58.658
You, big hairy guy.

01:07:58.742 --> 01:08:00.786
Block everything that
the kid throws your way.

01:08:00.869 --> 01:08:03.789
And you,
that's 12 feet of grizzly.

01:08:03.872 --> 01:08:05.207
Figure it out.

01:08:06.082 --> 01:08:07.083
Blocked.

01:08:08.752 --> 01:08:10.086
- Blocked.
- Dang.

01:08:10.587 --> 01:08:11.588
- Hey.
- Blocked.

01:08:12.088 --> 01:08:14.216
- [exclaims] Blocked.
- [whistle blows]

01:08:14.299 --> 01:08:18.053
Will, you gotta find a way
to get your shot over him.

01:08:18.136 --> 01:08:19.137
And Modo--

01:08:19.221 --> 01:08:21.681
Wait, wait.
Say it with your mind.

01:08:22.349 --> 01:08:24.142
Message!

01:08:24.226 --> 01:08:25.227
Yeah, yeah.

01:08:25.977 --> 01:08:28.188
[grunts] Received.

01:08:28.271 --> 01:08:30.649
If you do all this,
you'll be more than a team.

01:08:30.732 --> 01:08:33.443
You'll be a unit. Unstoppable.

01:08:33.527 --> 01:08:34.611
[team members] Roots run deep!

01:08:34.694 --> 01:08:36.071
"Goat Tears" is wack,

01:08:36.154 --> 01:08:37.781
- and I can't let it stand.
- [hip-hop music playing]

01:08:37.864 --> 01:08:41.660
So, Will,
I've prepared a little something

01:08:41.743 --> 01:08:43.954
to say "thank you"
for pushing us this far.

01:08:44.955 --> 01:08:46.289
♪ <i>That's my squad</i>
<i>That's my squad</i> ♪

01:08:46.373 --> 01:08:48.834
Here you go, Ms. Fillmore.
Can I get a picture?

01:08:48.917 --> 01:08:49.918
[camera shutter clicks]

01:08:50.001 --> 01:08:52.671
♪ <i>Shout out to my squad</i>
<i>Throw me the alley-oop</i> ♪

01:08:52.754 --> 01:08:54.047
♪ <i>I'm always at the top...</i> ♪

01:08:54.130 --> 01:08:55.340
No way.

01:08:55.423 --> 01:08:56.758
Nice to meet you, Theo.

01:08:56.842 --> 01:08:59.469
And this is for your dad.

01:09:00.345 --> 01:09:02.055
♪ <i>We not horsin' round</i>
<i>With you, okay</i> ♪

01:09:02.138 --> 01:09:04.891
Uno reverse.
You like that, Modo?

01:09:04.975 --> 01:09:06.184
- Give me some.
- [singsongy] Uno.

01:09:06.268 --> 01:09:08.019
[Lenny] ♪ <i>Sorry, horsey</i>
<i>Gotta roast ya</i> ♪

01:09:08.103 --> 01:09:09.646
♪ <i>Looks like Mr. Pony</i>
<i>Turnin' into Mr. Phony</i> ♪

01:09:09.729 --> 01:09:11.022
Will.

01:09:11.106 --> 01:09:14.317
♪ <i>Lenny G the one and only</i>
<i>And I always got my homeys</i> ♪

01:09:14.401 --> 01:09:15.944
Slamalamadingdong!

01:09:16.027 --> 01:09:18.238
♪ <i>That's my squad, hey</i>
<i>That's my squad, hey</i> ♪

01:09:18.321 --> 01:09:19.239
Olivia.

01:09:19.322 --> 01:09:20.740
♪ <i>I love my squad, hey</i> ♪

01:09:20.824 --> 01:09:21.950
Yo, Lenny!

01:09:23.368 --> 01:09:26.246
♪ <i>Shout out to my squad</i>
<i>Throw me the alley-oop</i> ♪

01:09:26.329 --> 01:09:27.455
♪ <i>I'm always at the top</i> ♪

01:09:27.539 --> 01:09:29.791
♪ <i>'Cause I'm taller than</i>
<i>The hoop</i> ♪

01:09:29.875 --> 01:09:31.084
- Horns on, everybody.
- [exclaims]

01:09:31.167 --> 01:09:33.420
[Chuck] <i>Thorns have really</i>
<i>found their groove.</i>

01:09:33.503 --> 01:09:36.172
<i>And is it me, or is Modo looking</i>
<i>different these days?</i>

01:09:36.256 --> 01:09:38.758
[Rusty] <i>Oh, yeah.</i>
<i>He's a thirst trap, Chuck.</i>

01:09:38.842 --> 01:09:40.343
Go long for my skin.

01:09:40.427 --> 01:09:41.803
Marry me, Modo.

01:09:41.887 --> 01:09:43.680
No, marry me! [groans]

01:09:43.763 --> 01:09:45.056
- Whoo!
- [crowd] Thorns! Thorns!

01:09:45.140 --> 01:09:47.767
[Chuck] The Thorns punch
their ticket to the Roar Four

01:09:47.851 --> 01:09:49.436
and are heading to the playoffs.

01:09:49.519 --> 01:09:51.605
[Rusty]
What a turnaround, Chuck!

01:09:51.688 --> 01:09:54.524
<i>If I were Mane, I'd be shaking</i>
<i>in my horseshoes</i>

01:09:54.608 --> 01:09:56.818
<i>'cause the Thorns</i>
<i>are coming for him.</i>

01:09:56.902 --> 01:10:00.280
[Lenny] ♪ <i>Looks like Mr. Pony</i>
<i>Turnin' into Mr. Phony...</i> ♪

01:10:00.363 --> 01:10:03.658
Do we have a deal? [chuckles]

01:10:03.742 --> 01:10:04.743
Good.

01:10:04.826 --> 01:10:05.660
Coach Dennis,

01:10:05.744 --> 01:10:08.246
how about a comment on
this team's epic turnaround?

01:10:08.330 --> 01:10:09.581
- How's it feel, Dennis?
- [song ends]

01:10:09.664 --> 01:10:12.459
It feels like victory!

01:10:12.542 --> 01:10:14.544
["Meets The Eye" playing]

01:10:15.420 --> 01:10:18.214
♪ <i>It's more than meets the eye </i>♪

01:10:18.298 --> 01:10:20.175
[chuckles]

01:10:21.551 --> 01:10:22.552
Yay!

01:10:22.636 --> 01:10:25.347
Okay, didn't know an ostrich
could get that fly.

01:10:25.430 --> 01:10:26.431
I see you, Olivia.

01:10:26.514 --> 01:10:27.599
You know what they say,

01:10:27.682 --> 01:10:30.936
birds of a feather
look fly together.

01:10:31.019 --> 01:10:34.147
[chuckles]
Archie's a whole vibe.

01:10:34.230 --> 01:10:38.026
[chuckles] Yeah, buddy.
I look good and I play good.

01:10:38.109 --> 01:10:39.611
[laughs]

01:10:39.694 --> 01:10:43.698
If Modo were any more of
a snack, he'd eat himself.

01:10:43.782 --> 01:10:45.659
Love it. Love it.

01:10:45.742 --> 01:10:46.743
Uh...

01:10:47.243 --> 01:10:49.079
[stammers] I'll be right back.

01:10:49.162 --> 01:10:50.163
[song ends]

01:10:50.246 --> 01:10:52.082
Uh... Anyone know where Jett is?

01:10:52.165 --> 01:10:53.208
I'll go get her.

01:10:53.833 --> 01:10:55.335
[announcer]
<i>From the Vineland Thorns,</i>

01:10:55.418 --> 01:10:57.963
<i>at guard, Jett Fillmore!</i>

01:10:58.046 --> 01:10:59.589
I sold this team.

01:11:00.256 --> 01:11:03.802
The new Thorns are relocating
to Sunken City.

01:11:03.885 --> 01:11:06.846
- I'm sorry, what? You're joking.
- [chuckles]

01:11:06.930 --> 01:11:10.266
Oh, I never joke about
money, honey.

01:11:10.350 --> 01:11:13.144
I brought Will onto this team
to put butts in seats,

01:11:13.228 --> 01:11:16.064
but I didn't expect
for you to actually win.

01:11:16.147 --> 01:11:18.108
I'm selling
while the getting's good.

01:11:18.191 --> 01:11:20.527
[stammers] What's gonna happen
to the team?

01:11:20.610 --> 01:11:25.532
Oh, they're all gone, sweetie.
[chuckles] Cleaning house.

01:11:25.615 --> 01:11:29.160
And as for you... [chuckles]

01:11:29.244 --> 01:11:35.500
I made sure the new owners knew
all about your worn-out body.

01:11:35.583 --> 01:11:38.003
And surprise, surprise,

01:11:38.086 --> 01:11:40.547
they weren't about to
waste money

01:11:40.630 --> 01:11:43.800
on an old, broken-down player

01:11:43.883 --> 01:11:46.428
who's never gonna win a Claw!

01:11:46.511 --> 01:11:48.388
- [Jett growls]
- Oh.

01:11:48.471 --> 01:11:52.934
And tell the team to clean out
their lockers after y'all lose.

01:11:53.018 --> 01:11:56.730
Enjoy your
early retirement, Jett.

01:11:57.355 --> 01:11:59.899
Hey, good luck
out there tonight.

01:11:59.983 --> 01:12:02.694
[chuckles, slurps]

01:12:02.777 --> 01:12:03.903
[Jett sighs]

01:12:03.987 --> 01:12:06.114
Jett, Flo sold the Thorns?

01:12:06.197 --> 01:12:07.782
You listening in
on my conversations now?

01:12:07.866 --> 01:12:09.034
- We need to go tell the team.
- [Jett] No,

01:12:09.117 --> 01:12:10.201
we'll tell them after the game.

01:12:10.285 --> 01:12:12.120
If we tell them now,
they'll fall apart.

01:12:12.203 --> 01:12:13.288
This affects all of us.

01:12:13.371 --> 01:12:15.832
Whatever's coming,
we got to face it together.

01:12:15.915 --> 01:12:18.209
Who's team captain here?
You or me?

01:12:18.293 --> 01:12:20.503
- Jett.
- After the game.

01:12:24.132 --> 01:12:26.134
[Chuck]
<i>Welcome to the Cryosphere.</i>

01:12:26.217 --> 01:12:28.720
<i>Tonight,</i>
<i>the Shivers face the Thorns</i>

01:12:28.803 --> 01:12:30.764
<i>in the semi-final game.</i>

01:12:30.847 --> 01:12:33.266
<i>The winner marches</i>
<i>triumphantly to the finals</i>

01:12:33.349 --> 01:12:36.895
<i>to battle for a championship</i>
<i>and eternal glory.</i>

01:12:36.978 --> 01:12:40.273
<i>The loser? Banished to</i>
<i>the cold void of history.</i>

01:12:40.356 --> 01:12:41.941
<i>This is not just a game.</i>

01:12:42.025 --> 01:12:43.818
<i>It is a reckoning.</i>

01:12:43.902 --> 01:12:45.445
[dramatic music playing]

01:12:47.030 --> 01:12:48.031
[growls]

01:12:48.823 --> 01:12:49.824
[groans]

01:12:49.908 --> 01:12:50.825
[grunts, growls]

01:12:50.909 --> 01:12:53.912
Lenny,
are you trying to get traded?

01:12:53.995 --> 01:12:55.288
Hey, hey, Jett, you good?

01:12:55.371 --> 01:12:56.790
Focus on the game.

01:12:57.332 --> 01:12:59.209
Don't worry about it.
We'll get the next one.

01:13:00.543 --> 01:13:02.378
- Olivia.
- [Olivia gasps]

01:13:02.462 --> 01:13:03.379
One more pass.

01:13:03.463 --> 01:13:05.507
Next time you think
about shooting, don't.

01:13:05.590 --> 01:13:08.051
[gasps] I'm sorry, Jett.

01:13:08.134 --> 01:13:10.136
- [Chuck] <i>And that's the half.</i>
- [buzzer sounds]

01:13:11.763 --> 01:13:12.764
Maybe we should tell them now.

01:13:12.847 --> 01:13:14.474
After the game.

01:13:20.647 --> 01:13:23.149
[panting]

01:13:23.233 --> 01:13:24.692
[opponent]
Don't hurt yourself, grandma.

01:13:24.776 --> 01:13:27.112
Catch! Yeah!

01:13:27.195 --> 01:13:28.780
[roars]

01:13:28.863 --> 01:13:31.116
[Chuck] <i>Oh! The icebreaker!</i>

01:13:31.199 --> 01:13:33.326
<i>And Harris is slow to get up.</i>

01:13:33.409 --> 01:13:35.036
So much for that Claw.
[chuckles]

01:13:35.120 --> 01:13:35.954
[Will] Thanks.

01:13:36.037 --> 01:13:38.498
[Chuck] <i>Thorns are down by 15</i>
<i>late in the fourth quarter.</i>

01:13:38.581 --> 01:13:41.417
[Rusty] <i>It is not looking good</i>
<i>for their playoff hopes.</i>

01:13:41.960 --> 01:13:44.129
What is going on out there?

01:13:44.212 --> 01:13:46.673
Jett, tell them.
They need to know.

01:13:46.756 --> 01:13:47.799
What did I say?

01:13:47.882 --> 01:13:50.135
Flo sold the team
to Sunken City.

01:13:50.218 --> 01:13:52.387
None of us are going with it.

01:13:52.470 --> 01:13:53.805
Can she even do that?
Is that even allowed?

01:13:53.888 --> 01:13:55.640
We were playing well.
We just started jelling.

01:13:55.723 --> 01:13:57.600
- She sold our team?
- [Olivia] There are rules.

01:13:57.684 --> 01:13:58.977
[fan 1] <i>I thought you had</i>
<i>a championship.</i>

01:13:59.060 --> 01:14:00.478
[fan 2] <i>Could have been</i>
<i>a legend, instead...</i>

01:14:00.562 --> 01:14:05.275
[Flo] <i>Broken-down player</i>
<i>who's never gonna win a Claw!</i>

01:14:05.358 --> 01:14:07.318
Just get me the ball.

01:14:07.402 --> 01:14:09.237
I'm not going out like this.

01:14:09.320 --> 01:14:11.281
Don't you mean "we"?

01:14:11.364 --> 01:14:13.408
I know that look.

01:14:13.491 --> 01:14:14.784
[growls]

01:14:17.871 --> 01:14:19.622
What do you think you're doing?

01:14:20.331 --> 01:14:22.125
[Chuck] <i>That's two.</i>
<i>Thorns down by ten.</i>

01:14:22.208 --> 01:14:23.418
Come on.

01:14:23.918 --> 01:14:26.004
- We got to D up.
- [grunts]

01:14:26.087 --> 01:14:27.630
Somebody get a body on her.

01:14:28.756 --> 01:14:29.841
Come on.

01:14:29.924 --> 01:14:31.050
[growls]

01:14:31.134 --> 01:14:31.968
Pass!

01:14:32.051 --> 01:14:33.928
[Chuck] <i>Oh,</i>
<i>we've seen this before, Rusty.</i>

01:14:34.012 --> 01:14:36.973
<i>It's the Jett Fillmore show now.</i>

01:14:37.056 --> 01:14:38.975
<i>Jett with the pull-up.</i>
<i>Thorns down eight.</i>

01:14:39.058 --> 01:14:40.435
[panting]

01:14:40.935 --> 01:14:41.936
[groans]

01:14:42.020 --> 01:14:43.146
Heads up!

01:14:45.148 --> 01:14:46.941
[Chuck]
<i>That deficit is cut to five.</i>

01:14:48.651 --> 01:14:50.278
<i>It's a one-point game.</i>

01:14:50.361 --> 01:14:51.404
Ball! Now!

01:14:51.487 --> 01:14:53.198
[Chuck]
<i>It all comes down to this!</i>

01:14:53.281 --> 01:14:55.033
- Archie!
- Give me that, small.

01:14:55.116 --> 01:14:56.367
- [Will] Boost me!
- [groans]

01:14:56.451 --> 01:14:57.619
[grunts]

01:14:58.536 --> 01:15:00.914
[Rusty] <i>Will Harris for the win!</i>

01:15:04.500 --> 01:15:05.752
- [Jett] Yeah!
- [buzzer sounds]

01:15:05.835 --> 01:15:08.755
[Chuck] <i>Thorns win! Thorns win!</i>

01:15:08.838 --> 01:15:10.965
<i>They're headed to the Claw!</i>

01:15:14.928 --> 01:15:17.639
[pants] So it looks like
we're going to the...

01:15:19.891 --> 01:15:20.975
to the finals.

01:15:24.312 --> 01:15:27.565
Wow. I-I'm done.
Team's sold anyway.

01:15:27.649 --> 01:15:28.483
Come on, girls.

01:15:28.566 --> 01:15:29.651
I'm not sticking around
for this.

01:15:29.734 --> 01:15:30.944
Modo as well.

01:15:32.695 --> 01:15:34.197
[melancholy music playing]

01:15:34.280 --> 01:15:35.156
[Will sighs]

01:15:35.657 --> 01:15:37.742
You used to be
my favorite player.

01:15:38.618 --> 01:15:39.744
Until today.

01:15:40.995 --> 01:15:42.789
[Rusty] <i>What a turn of events.</i>

01:15:42.872 --> 01:15:45.124
<i>The Thorns have</i>
<i>a shot at the Claw,</i>

01:15:45.208 --> 01:15:47.502
<i>but Vineland has</i>
<i>lost their team.</i>

01:15:47.585 --> 01:15:49.921
[Chuck] <i>I'll tell you, Rusty,</i>
<i>I would hate to be a Thorns fan</i>

01:15:50.004 --> 01:15:51.214
<i>right about now.</i>

01:15:51.923 --> 01:15:53.424
["Don't Dream It's Over"
playing]

01:15:53.508 --> 01:15:55.843
♪ <i>There is freedom within</i> ♪

01:15:55.927 --> 01:15:57.720
♪ <i>There is freedom without</i> ♪

01:15:57.804 --> 01:16:01.015
♪ <i>Try to catch the deluge</i>
<i>In a paper cup</i> ♪

01:16:04.310 --> 01:16:07.105
♪ <i>There's a battle ahead </i>♪

01:16:07.188 --> 01:16:09.357
♪ <i>Many battles are lost </i>♪

01:16:09.440 --> 01:16:11.150
♪ <i>But you'll never see</i>
<i>The end of the road </i>♪

01:16:11.234 --> 01:16:14.362
♪ <i>While you're traveling</i>
<i>With me </i>♪

01:16:15.113 --> 01:16:16.906
♪ <i>Hey now, hey now </i>♪

01:16:16.990 --> 01:16:19.826
♪ <i>Don't dream it's over </i>♪

01:16:19.909 --> 01:16:23.454
♪ <i>Hey now, hey now</i> ♪

01:16:23.538 --> 01:16:25.999
♪ <i>When the world comes in </i>♪

01:16:26.082 --> 01:16:29.419
♪ <i>They come, they come </i>♪

01:16:29.502 --> 01:16:32.547
♪ <i>To build a wall between us </i>♪

01:16:32.630 --> 01:16:36.259
♪<i> We know they won't win</i> ♪

01:16:39.053 --> 01:16:41.848
♪ <i>Now I'm towing my car </i>♪

01:16:41.931 --> 01:16:43.975
♪ <i>There's a hole in the roof </i>♪

01:16:44.058 --> 01:16:46.185
♪ <i>My possessions</i>
<i>Are causing me suspicion </i>♪

01:16:46.269 --> 01:16:48.688
♪ <i>But there's no proof</i> ♪

01:16:50.606 --> 01:16:52.775
♪ <i>In the paper today </i>♪

01:16:52.859 --> 01:16:55.611
♪ <i>Tales of war and of waste </i>♪

01:16:55.695 --> 01:16:59.449
♪ <i>But you turn right over</i>
<i>To the TV page </i>♪

01:17:01.409 --> 01:17:03.578
♪ <i>Hey now, hey now </i>♪

01:17:03.661 --> 01:17:05.330
♪ <i>Don't dream it's over </i>♪

01:17:05.413 --> 01:17:06.414
[song ends]

01:17:06.497 --> 01:17:08.166
Come on. Let's go!

01:17:08.249 --> 01:17:09.459
- [pants]
- [bleats]

01:17:09.542 --> 01:17:10.668
I got it! [grunts]

01:17:10.752 --> 01:17:12.045
[all cheering]

01:17:12.128 --> 01:17:13.880
[Grizz] Smalls can ball.

01:17:13.963 --> 01:17:17.091
- Whew! [chuckles]
- Yeah!

01:17:17.175 --> 01:17:18.760
- [scoffs] No way.
- Wait, is that...

01:17:18.843 --> 01:17:19.927
[all] Hey, Will.

01:17:20.762 --> 01:17:22.555
Goat? Ball.

01:17:24.515 --> 01:17:26.851
Yo, shouldn't you be getting
ready to face the Magma?

01:17:26.934 --> 01:17:28.644
Did you not watch the game?

01:17:28.728 --> 01:17:30.813
I don't think Jett
wants to play with us anymore.

01:17:30.897 --> 01:17:33.107
I'm willing to bet she does.

01:17:34.108 --> 01:17:36.903
Hey. Can we talk?

01:17:36.986 --> 01:17:37.987
I'm busy.

01:17:38.071 --> 01:17:39.197
- No, he's not.
- Come on, come on.

01:17:39.280 --> 01:17:41.949
- Give... Give me the ball.
- Not happening. My ball now.

01:17:43.951 --> 01:17:47.455
I came to say I'm-I'm sorry.

01:17:47.538 --> 01:17:49.749
Okay. Well, you did it. So...

01:17:49.832 --> 01:17:52.752
Please, just hear me out?

01:17:54.629 --> 01:17:56.964
[inhales, sighs]

01:17:57.632 --> 01:17:59.592
I want to win.

01:18:00.593 --> 01:18:02.011
I want to hold up that Claw

01:18:02.095 --> 01:18:05.640
and feel what it's like
to be one of the greats.

01:18:06.599 --> 01:18:09.644
When Flo said all that stuff
about me being washed up,

01:18:10.144 --> 01:18:11.521
it just... it-it...

01:18:12.355 --> 01:18:13.648
it just got in my head.

01:18:14.273 --> 01:18:18.403
And I couldn't let it go because
deep down, deep, deep down,

01:18:19.237 --> 01:18:20.947
I'm scared she's right.

01:18:21.572 --> 01:18:23.825
And I just panicked. [pants]

01:18:23.908 --> 01:18:25.868
And I did you all so dirty.

01:18:25.952 --> 01:18:29.455
And I'm so...
[inhales sharply] ...sorry.

01:18:33.126 --> 01:18:34.919
You know, I really thought that

01:18:35.002 --> 01:18:37.588
if I was holding a Claw
at the end of the day,

01:18:37.672 --> 01:18:39.799
it wouldn't matter how I got it.

01:18:39.882 --> 01:18:41.467
But when you think about it,

01:18:41.551 --> 01:18:43.719
that's kind of all that matters.

01:18:43.803 --> 01:18:48.349
[chuckles]
That was a really good apology.

01:18:48.433 --> 01:18:52.520
But you know,
you still owe the diner a Claw.

01:18:53.521 --> 01:18:55.773
It's gonna be hard to win
without a team.

01:18:55.857 --> 01:18:57.817
I might know a few folks.

01:18:57.900 --> 01:18:59.444
- [doorbell rings]
- [footsteps thud]

01:18:59.527 --> 01:19:00.736
- [child 1] Dad.
- [child 2] Daddy clown!

01:19:00.820 --> 01:19:02.321
- Oh, thank God.
- [twins clamoring]

01:19:02.405 --> 01:19:03.739
These girls are crazy.

01:19:03.823 --> 01:19:06.492
Get me out of here.
Quick, start the car!

01:19:06.576 --> 01:19:07.743
[tapping on window]

01:19:10.455 --> 01:19:12.373
- [squeaks]
- Yo.

01:19:12.498 --> 01:19:13.791
[Olivia chirping]

01:19:15.042 --> 01:19:16.043
Sup, Olivia?

01:19:16.127 --> 01:19:18.171
Come on.
We've got a game to win.

01:19:18.254 --> 01:19:19.255
Yes!

01:19:19.797 --> 01:19:22.258
[mysterious music playing]

01:19:22.341 --> 01:19:25.136
[growls, hisses]

01:19:26.262 --> 01:19:29.557
[chortles, rasps]

01:19:29.640 --> 01:19:31.642
[suspenseful music playing]

01:19:34.353 --> 01:19:35.354
[crowd cheering]

01:19:38.149 --> 01:19:40.234
[music continues]

01:19:40.318 --> 01:19:42.528
[Chuck] <i>This is what dreams</i>
<i>are made of, Rusty.</i>

01:19:42.612 --> 01:19:44.822
- [blusters]
- [Chuck] <i>Teams become champions.</i>

01:19:44.906 --> 01:19:46.949
<i>Players become legends.</i>

01:19:50.077 --> 01:19:51.996
- ♪ <i>Let's go </i>♪
- ♪ <i>Yeah </i>♪

01:19:52.079 --> 01:19:53.915
♪ <i>Gimme the ball</i>
<i>Gimme the ball, yeah </i>♪

01:19:53.998 --> 01:19:55.833
- ♪ <i>Let's go! </i>♪
- ♪ <i>Oh, I'm 'bout to... </i>♪

01:19:55.917 --> 01:19:58.294
- Go, Thorns!
- The best day of my life.

01:19:58.377 --> 01:19:59.837
I can feel myself
getting invested.

01:19:59.921 --> 01:20:03.174
Who cares? I'm here for it.
Break my heart, kiddo!

01:20:03.257 --> 01:20:05.176
Come on, Will. Let's go!

01:20:05.259 --> 01:20:06.844
[all] Go, Thorns! Go, Thorns!

01:20:06.928 --> 01:20:08.179
[Chuck] <i>Tonight, Jett and Mane</i>

01:20:08.262 --> 01:20:10.056
<i>will finally answer</i>
<i>the question,</i>

01:20:10.139 --> 01:20:12.266
- <i>who is the GOAT?</i>
- On three.

01:20:12.350 --> 01:20:14.393
- One, two, three.
- [all] Roots run deep!

01:20:14.477 --> 01:20:15.728
- [crowd cheering]
- [song ends]

01:20:15.811 --> 01:20:18.064
[Rusty] <i>And here we go, Chuck.</i>

01:20:19.357 --> 01:20:20.816
<i>Unbelievable!</i>

01:20:20.900 --> 01:20:23.319
<i>Mane Attraction</i>
<i>gets the tip over Lenny.</i>

01:20:23.402 --> 01:20:25.404
[pants, grunts]

01:20:25.488 --> 01:20:26.614
[groans]

01:20:27.156 --> 01:20:28.991
[Chuck] <i>Mane drills one home,</i>

01:20:29.075 --> 01:20:31.035
<i>sending a strong message</i>
<i>to the Thorns.</i>

01:20:31.536 --> 01:20:32.662
[chuckles]

01:20:34.080 --> 01:20:36.749
You're too small. [spits]

01:20:37.416 --> 01:20:40.586
Come on, Will.
Show 'em who's too small.

01:20:41.504 --> 01:20:42.588
[whistle blows]

01:20:45.466 --> 01:20:46.926
Eyes on me. [growls]

01:20:48.010 --> 01:20:49.637
[Rusty]
<i>Jett with the sweet pass.</i>

01:20:50.179 --> 01:20:51.013
<i>Thorns respond.</i>

01:20:51.097 --> 01:20:52.098
- [all cheering]
- Yeah!

01:20:52.682 --> 01:20:54.559
[Chuck] <i>As the first quarter</i>
<i>comes to a close,</i>

01:20:54.642 --> 01:20:56.852
<i>it's still anyone's game.</i>

01:20:56.936 --> 01:20:59.522
[whinnies] We should be
frying these fools.

01:20:59.605 --> 01:21:03.359
Take 'em out if you have to, but
hold on to that lead.

01:21:04.360 --> 01:21:05.695
[all grunting]

01:21:07.029 --> 01:21:08.072
[Rusty] <i>Harris on a break!</i>

01:21:08.155 --> 01:21:09.657
Nuh-uh! Not today!

01:21:09.740 --> 01:21:11.742
- Will, watch out!
- Huh?

01:21:11.826 --> 01:21:13.494
[groans]

01:21:13.578 --> 01:21:15.413
[Chuck] <i>Ow! Hard hit on Jett.</i>

01:21:15.496 --> 01:21:16.831
- <i>No foul call.</i>
- [buzzer sounds]

01:21:18.291 --> 01:21:19.292
What?

01:21:19.375 --> 01:21:21.294
[groans, shrieks]

01:21:21.377 --> 01:21:22.587
[inhales sharply]

01:21:23.170 --> 01:21:24.630
Oh, no.

01:21:26.507 --> 01:21:27.925
[grunting, panting]

01:21:28.009 --> 01:21:30.219
This injury could
take you out permanently

01:21:30.303 --> 01:21:32.430
if you put any more weight
on this leg.

01:21:32.513 --> 01:21:35.641
[groans, sniffles]
I'm sorry, y'all.

01:21:35.725 --> 01:21:39.395
Jett. I didn't mean
for you to get hurt.

01:21:39.478 --> 01:21:41.314
Hey, hey. It's not your fault.

01:21:42.023 --> 01:21:44.859
But I think I'm done.

01:21:46.485 --> 01:21:47.403
What are we gonna do?

01:21:47.486 --> 01:21:49.196
We can't win without Jett.

01:21:49.280 --> 01:21:51.824
What? Aw, we're all thinking it.

01:21:51.907 --> 01:21:53.909
[melancholy music playing]

01:22:00.708 --> 01:22:01.709
[sighs]

01:22:02.627 --> 01:22:07.632
Look, "roots run deep,"
that's more than just a cheer.

01:22:08.299 --> 01:22:11.552
You guys have no idea
what you mean to this city.

01:22:12.345 --> 01:22:15.556
My mom told me to dream big.

01:22:16.140 --> 01:22:17.391
And for Vineland,

01:22:17.475 --> 01:22:21.479
there is no dream bigger
than bringing home a Claw.

01:22:21.562 --> 01:22:24.482
This might be the last time
Vineland Thorns ever play.

01:22:24.565 --> 01:22:26.359
And we ain't
gonna go out like this.

01:22:26.442 --> 01:22:28.527
Yeah, you heard the rook.

01:22:28.611 --> 01:22:32.114
[inhales, growls]
Let's dream big.

01:22:41.499 --> 01:22:43.084
Is that-- Is that Jett?

01:22:43.167 --> 01:22:45.211
- Did she just--
- Yeah, Jett!

01:22:45.294 --> 01:22:47.296
[crowd exclaiming, cheering]

01:22:52.385 --> 01:22:55.971
[crowd chanting]
Jett, Jett, Jett!

01:22:56.055 --> 01:22:58.391
[Chuck] <i>A well-deserved</i>
<i>standing ovation</i>

01:22:58.474 --> 01:23:01.102
<i>for the legendary Jett Fillmore.</i>

01:23:01.185 --> 01:23:02.645
[chanting continues]

01:23:05.356 --> 01:23:06.607
Welcome back, GOAT.

01:23:06.691 --> 01:23:09.777
[crowd chanting rapidly]
Jett! Jett! Jett!

01:23:11.362 --> 01:23:12.279
Archie.

01:23:12.363 --> 01:23:13.447
[grunts]

01:23:14.156 --> 01:23:15.866
[Chuck] <i>Harris is on a tear.</i>

01:23:16.367 --> 01:23:17.993
<i>The Thorns are all tied up.</i>

01:23:18.911 --> 01:23:20.913
- Olivia!
- I got this.

01:23:20.996 --> 01:23:22.581
[roars]

01:23:24.709 --> 01:23:25.835
[cackles]

01:23:29.672 --> 01:23:31.006
I am that bird.

01:23:31.090 --> 01:23:32.967
I am that bird.

01:23:33.050 --> 01:23:34.051
[grunts]

01:23:35.469 --> 01:23:37.972
[majestic music playing]

01:23:38.055 --> 01:23:39.807
[both] She can fly!

01:23:39.890 --> 01:23:41.851
I can fly!

01:23:41.934 --> 01:23:43.686
She can fly?

01:23:43.769 --> 01:23:45.187
[whinnies]

01:23:45.271 --> 01:23:48.899
[Chuck] <i>Olivia Burke</i>
<i>just posterized Mane!</i>

01:23:48.983 --> 01:23:50.985
I am losing my mind here!

01:23:51.068 --> 01:23:52.778
- Olivia!
- [all cheering]

01:23:52.862 --> 01:23:54.864
- That's right.
- Go, Livvy!

01:23:54.947 --> 01:23:56.907
[all] Go, Thorns! We can do it!

01:23:56.991 --> 01:23:59.368
[Rusty] <i>Smalls ball!</i>
<i>Ostriches fly!</i>

01:23:59.452 --> 01:24:01.454
<i>These are the Thorns</i>
<i>we came to see!</i>

01:24:01.537 --> 01:24:03.706
Look who's the poster child now.

01:24:05.207 --> 01:24:06.208
[grunts, whinnies]

01:24:06.292 --> 01:24:08.002
- [blusters]
- [whistle blows]

01:24:08.085 --> 01:24:09.795
Time out, Magma.

01:24:09.879 --> 01:24:12.631
Oh, word of advice?
Stay off social media.

01:24:13.174 --> 01:24:15.301
We gotta turn this around now.

01:24:15.384 --> 01:24:19.680
- Where my Maniacs at?
- [all chanting] Mane!

01:24:19.764 --> 01:24:22.308
Uh-oh, I think we've got
some seismic activity.

01:24:22.391 --> 01:24:24.769
<i>Just listen to that crowd.</i>

01:24:24.852 --> 01:24:28.022
- <i>They're going crazy.</i>
- Oh, yeah!

01:24:28.564 --> 01:24:30.232
[Rusty] <i>Let's go!</i>

01:24:30.316 --> 01:24:31.609
[ominous music playing]

01:24:34.153 --> 01:24:37.031
- Archie's trapped. No way out.
- I know the feeling, Rusty.

01:24:37.698 --> 01:24:39.450
- <i>Whoa! And up goes Lenny.</i>
- [groans]

01:24:40.159 --> 01:24:41.327
[Mane chuckling]

01:24:42.244 --> 01:24:44.455
Jett can't save you now.

01:24:45.498 --> 01:24:46.499
[chuckles]

01:24:47.291 --> 01:24:49.210
[Rusty] <i>Ooh. Hard foul by Mane.</i>

01:24:49.293 --> 01:24:50.878
- What?
- You gotta call that!

01:24:50.961 --> 01:24:53.339
The zebra and the horse
are working together.

01:24:53.422 --> 01:24:54.965
- [all] Boo!
- Come on! That's a foul.

01:24:55.049 --> 01:24:56.258
[groans]

01:24:57.301 --> 01:24:59.929
Really? That's how
you want to win? Huh?

01:25:00.012 --> 01:25:02.139
What you gonna do
about it, small?

01:25:02.223 --> 01:25:03.474
Hey, Mane!

01:25:04.183 --> 01:25:06.435
He's not a small.

01:25:06.519 --> 01:25:11.357
He's a medium!

01:25:11.440 --> 01:25:13.526
- [referee] Hey, break it up!
- [whistle blows]

01:25:13.609 --> 01:25:15.486
Let me at him! Let me at him!

01:25:15.569 --> 01:25:17.112
- Relax!
- [whistle blows]

01:25:17.196 --> 01:25:19.114
- [groans]
- Keep your hooves

01:25:19.198 --> 01:25:20.491
off my teammates.

01:25:20.574 --> 01:25:21.742
Get him, Daddy!

01:25:21.826 --> 01:25:23.536
Make him bleed!

01:25:23.619 --> 01:25:25.120
That's not what you want to see.

01:25:25.204 --> 01:25:26.539
Speak for yourself.

01:25:26.622 --> 01:25:29.124
Flagrant two.
Number 34, ejected.

01:25:29.208 --> 01:25:31.544
Are you kidding me?
Mane started it.

01:25:31.627 --> 01:25:33.629
- Where's his foul?
- [Mane] Cry about it.

01:25:33.712 --> 01:25:36.090
[Chuck] <i>The rules state</i>
<i>Thorns need five players</i>

01:25:36.173 --> 01:25:37.258
- <i>or they forfeit.</i>
- Hit me again.

01:25:37.341 --> 01:25:38.342
[bell dings]

01:25:39.009 --> 01:25:41.011
[panting] Okay, okay.

01:25:41.095 --> 01:25:43.138
I haven't played since my
rec-league days,

01:25:43.222 --> 01:25:44.056
but I guess I could--

01:25:44.139 --> 01:25:45.432
[grunts]

01:25:45.516 --> 01:25:48.602
[snarls, growling]

01:25:49.645 --> 01:25:50.729
[grunts]

01:25:50.813 --> 01:25:52.064
Put me in, Coach.

01:25:52.565 --> 01:25:55.109
I got a game to win.

01:25:55.192 --> 01:25:57.611
- [laughs]
- [growls]

01:25:57.695 --> 01:25:59.321
Jett, you can barely walk.

01:25:59.405 --> 01:26:02.575
No. We can't let you do this.
You'll just make it worse.

01:26:02.658 --> 01:26:03.701
You think they bought it?

01:26:03.784 --> 01:26:04.827
[all gasp]

01:26:04.910 --> 01:26:06.078
Um, I do.

01:26:06.161 --> 01:26:09.164
I think we have about three
seconds before they catch on.

01:26:09.248 --> 01:26:11.041
But that's all we need.
You all ready?

01:26:11.125 --> 01:26:13.043
I've been trying to run a play
like this all season,

01:26:13.127 --> 01:26:15.921
but some hothead
kept interrupting me.

01:26:16.005 --> 01:26:17.840
That's a great play.

01:26:17.923 --> 01:26:19.842
Yeah. It was worth the wait.

01:26:22.803 --> 01:26:23.971
[all] Roots run deep!

01:26:24.054 --> 01:26:26.515
[Chuck] <i>The Thorns are down by 2</i>
<i>with 20 seconds on the clock.</i>

01:26:26.599 --> 01:26:29.894
[Rusty] <i>Jett's gonna lay it all</i>
<i>on the line. What a competitor!</i>

01:26:29.977 --> 01:26:31.645
Listen up. Double-team her.

01:26:31.729 --> 01:26:33.522
Triple-team her if you have to.

01:26:33.606 --> 01:26:35.900
Do not let her out
of your sight.

01:26:35.983 --> 01:26:38.569
[Chuck] <i>Jett's fighting an</i>
<i>injury. The court is unstable.</i>

01:26:38.652 --> 01:26:40.988
<i>Do you still want her</i>
<i>taking the final shot?</i>

01:26:41.071 --> 01:26:44.074
[Rusty] <i>With fire and brimstone</i>
<i>bringing judgment and wrath</i>

01:26:44.158 --> 01:26:46.869
<i>to us all, I want Fillmore!</i>

01:26:46.952 --> 01:26:49.455
[groans]

01:26:50.039 --> 01:26:52.249
[grunting]

01:26:54.001 --> 01:26:55.502
[all groaning, distorted]

01:27:01.258 --> 01:27:03.886
[climactic music playing]

01:27:03.969 --> 01:27:05.471
- Ah!
- [grunts]

01:27:06.388 --> 01:27:07.389
[snarls]

01:27:09.391 --> 01:27:10.517
[growling]

01:27:13.854 --> 01:27:14.939
- [leg crunches]
- [whimpers]

01:27:15.022 --> 01:27:16.398
[whinnies]

01:27:17.191 --> 01:27:18.567
[roars]

01:27:18.651 --> 01:27:19.944
[both growling]

01:27:25.074 --> 01:27:26.367
[growls]

01:27:26.450 --> 01:27:27.493
[growls]

01:27:29.203 --> 01:27:31.205
- Will!
- [panting]

01:27:32.873 --> 01:27:34.750
Come on. Get past me.

01:27:34.833 --> 01:27:36.001
I don't have to.

01:27:40.631 --> 01:27:41.423
[groans]

01:27:44.093 --> 01:27:46.345
[buzzer sounds]

01:27:46.428 --> 01:27:47.721
[music continues]

01:27:55.104 --> 01:27:57.356
- [music ends]
- [chain rattles]

01:28:05.280 --> 01:28:07.491
- [all cheering]
- [triumphant music playing]

01:28:09.785 --> 01:28:12.413
Our bestie just won the Claw.

01:28:12.496 --> 01:28:15.624
- That's my boy!
- Hold me, Daryl. [giggles]

01:28:15.708 --> 01:28:18.127
[Rusty] <i>For the first time</i>
<i>in 50 years,</i>

01:28:18.210 --> 01:28:20.087
the Vineland Thorns
are champions!

01:28:20.170 --> 01:28:22.047
Miracles can happen, folks.

01:28:22.131 --> 01:28:26.427
[chuckling] I love this game.
And I love you, Rusty.

01:28:26.510 --> 01:28:30.723
[sobbing]
I love you too, Chuckles.

01:28:30.806 --> 01:28:32.808
[uplifting music playing]

01:28:37.396 --> 01:28:39.356
- Attaboy, Will! Mwah!
- [all exclaiming]

01:28:39.440 --> 01:28:40.441
Honey!

01:28:40.524 --> 01:28:44.153
Let's have another
dozen kids. [chuckles]

01:28:44.236 --> 01:28:45.237
Ha-ha!

01:28:45.320 --> 01:28:49.783
Ten years, ten teams,
one Claw, baby!

01:28:49.867 --> 01:28:52.202
We are champions!

01:28:52.286 --> 01:28:53.537
- Daddy!
- Daddy!

01:28:53.620 --> 01:28:54.830
You were so cool.

01:28:54.913 --> 01:28:58.876
Daddy was pretty cool, right?
I was like... [roars]

01:28:58.959 --> 01:29:00.669
[both] We love you. Mwah.

01:29:00.753 --> 01:29:02.087
[chuckles] I love you girls.

01:29:02.171 --> 01:29:04.089
- [rasping]
- [twins giggling]

01:29:04.173 --> 01:29:06.258
- [blusters]
- Hey, Mane. Good game.

01:29:06.341 --> 01:29:07.342
Let me help you up.

01:29:09.178 --> 01:29:12.723
- Hey, uh, your hair is on fire.
- What?

01:29:12.806 --> 01:29:14.516
Oh, no. No. No.

01:29:14.600 --> 01:29:17.853
Not the hair! [sobbing]

01:29:19.104 --> 01:29:20.814
- [Jett] Will!
- Jett.

01:29:20.898 --> 01:29:22.608
We're champions, baby.

01:29:22.691 --> 01:29:25.027
Oh, Jett! We did it!
We actually did it!

01:29:25.110 --> 01:29:26.612
No, you did it.

01:29:26.695 --> 01:29:28.405
Looks like Moms was right.

01:29:31.533 --> 01:29:32.659
[groans]

01:29:32.743 --> 01:29:34.203
- J-Jett, you okay? You good?
- I'm fine.

01:29:34.286 --> 01:29:36.413
I'm fine. I just can't
feel my legs... [chuckling]

01:29:36.497 --> 01:29:38.749
...but I'm a champion, baby.

01:29:38.832 --> 01:29:41.251
[laughs] Never thought
I'd see the day

01:29:41.335 --> 01:29:43.295
Jett Fillmore passed the ball.

01:29:43.378 --> 01:29:44.379
[both] Security!

01:29:44.463 --> 01:29:45.672
[Flo] Hold up, sucka.

01:29:45.756 --> 01:29:49.051
- Playtime?
- Should we destroy?

01:29:49.676 --> 01:29:51.512
[both] Destroy! [giggling]

01:29:51.595 --> 01:29:54.389
[Flo] Do you know who I am?

01:29:54.473 --> 01:29:55.599
Hey, you were right about Will.

01:29:55.682 --> 01:29:57.476
He's a great addition
to the team.

01:29:57.559 --> 01:29:59.186
Bye, piglet.

01:29:59.728 --> 01:30:05.067
[announcer] Introducing
your Roar champions,

01:30:05.150 --> 01:30:07.361
the Vineland Thorns!

01:30:07.444 --> 01:30:10.280
- [all cheering]
- [upbeat music playing]

01:30:13.033 --> 01:30:16.120
Yeah! Let's go, Vineland!
Let's go!

01:30:16.203 --> 01:30:17.996
[all cheering]

01:30:18.080 --> 01:30:19.206
Horns up, everybody.

01:30:19.289 --> 01:30:20.916
Vineland!

01:30:21.750 --> 01:30:23.669
I think it's time
they hear from...

01:30:26.171 --> 01:30:27.923
- the GOAT.
- [crowd cheering]

01:30:28.006 --> 01:30:30.092
[all chanting] Will! Will! Will!

01:30:31.969 --> 01:30:33.345
Medium fries did it!

01:30:33.428 --> 01:30:34.930
[all whooping]

01:30:35.973 --> 01:30:37.933
[music continues]

01:30:38.016 --> 01:30:39.560
- I... I...
- [cheering stops]

01:30:39.643 --> 01:30:41.186
I don't even know
what to say right now.

01:30:41.270 --> 01:30:43.605
- [sighs] This is crazy.
- [fan] We love you, Will!

01:30:43.689 --> 01:30:45.732
Oh, wow, um...

01:30:46.441 --> 01:30:48.318
I mean... [scoffs]

01:30:48.986 --> 01:30:52.364
I saw Jett play when...
when I was just a kid.

01:30:53.198 --> 01:30:58.912
Then I told my mom, I said,
"I'm gonna be just like her."

01:30:58.996 --> 01:31:00.664
[atmospheric music playing]

01:31:00.747 --> 01:31:02.457
And you know what's crazy?

01:31:02.958 --> 01:31:05.502
My mom actually believed it.

01:31:06.128 --> 01:31:09.464
She always seemed to know
those kinds of things, you know?

01:31:09.548 --> 01:31:15.345
Like she always knew that even
if she couldn't be here for me,

01:31:15.429 --> 01:31:17.556
- Vineland would be.
- [crowd cheering]

01:31:17.639 --> 01:31:19.683
You delivered for me...

01:31:19.766 --> 01:31:21.435
Will done changed the game.

01:31:22.060 --> 01:31:24.396
And you always had my back.

01:31:24.479 --> 01:31:26.106
[both bleating]

01:31:26.190 --> 01:31:28.442
And you inspired me.

01:31:28.525 --> 01:31:30.777
[all chuckling]

01:31:30.861 --> 01:31:34.364
We brought the Claw home!

01:31:34.448 --> 01:31:36.950
[all cheering]

01:31:40.120 --> 01:31:42.080
And even if the Thorns

01:31:42.164 --> 01:31:44.124
don't have a home
in Vineland anymore...

01:31:44.208 --> 01:31:45.209
[crowd booing]

01:31:45.292 --> 01:31:46.460
[sobbing]

01:31:46.543 --> 01:31:47.544
[blows nose]

01:31:48.420 --> 01:31:52.257
...no one can take
this Claw away from us!

01:31:52.341 --> 01:31:53.342
[cheering resumes]

01:31:55.761 --> 01:31:58.972
Vineland will be
champions forever!

01:32:00.974 --> 01:32:03.352
- Modo has something to say!
- [cheering stops]

01:32:04.269 --> 01:32:08.857
Thorns staying in Vineland!

01:32:08.941 --> 01:32:10.234
[all gasp]

01:32:10.317 --> 01:32:13.320
- Modo is team owner.
- [crowd exclaiming]

01:32:13.403 --> 01:32:14.613
Wait. How?

01:32:14.696 --> 01:32:16.156
[dramatic music playing]

01:32:19.660 --> 01:32:20.994
All in.

01:32:21.078 --> 01:32:22.329
[opponent] All in.

01:32:22.412 --> 01:32:25.207
A-ha! Uno reverse!

01:32:25.290 --> 01:32:26.959
- What?
- Let me take a look at that.

01:32:27.042 --> 01:32:29.795
You're giving this
freak lizard the team?

01:32:29.878 --> 01:32:32.798
Wow! This is actually legit.

01:32:32.881 --> 01:32:34.424
[chuckling] Modo's my boss.

01:32:34.508 --> 01:32:36.343
- That's not good.
- [all whooping]

01:32:36.426 --> 01:32:37.970
Yeah, mama!

01:32:38.053 --> 01:32:40.013
[rasps, muttering]

01:32:40.097 --> 01:32:42.349
- [chuckling] Modo.
- [vocalizing]

01:32:42.432 --> 01:32:45.978
[all chuckling]

01:32:46.061 --> 01:32:48.605
- [fan 1] Marry me, Modo!
- [fan 2] No, marry me!

01:32:48.689 --> 01:32:50.565
You hear that, Vineland?

01:32:50.649 --> 01:32:54.903
Looks like the Thorns
are staying!

01:32:54.987 --> 01:32:58.156
[all chanting]
Roots run deep! Roots run deep!

01:33:02.619 --> 01:33:03.996
[chanting continues]

01:33:04.079 --> 01:33:05.455
Roots run deep!

01:33:05.539 --> 01:33:06.665
Roots run deep!

01:33:06.748 --> 01:33:08.000
Roots run deep!

01:33:08.083 --> 01:33:13.255
[chanting continues]

01:33:13.338 --> 01:33:15.132
[all exclaiming]

01:33:16.008 --> 01:33:18.343
[bleats]

01:33:18.427 --> 01:33:20.304
[chuckles]

01:33:22.347 --> 01:33:24.474
[atmospheric music playing]

01:33:27.644 --> 01:33:29.062
[Young Will] <i>Thanks, Mom.</i>

01:33:34.735 --> 01:33:36.737
["I'm Good" playing]

01:33:41.158 --> 01:33:43.201
♪ <i>Whoo! Come on </i>♪

01:33:45.203 --> 01:33:48.790
